1
00:00:14,014 --> 00:00:17,984
A makeover project
for your most unhinged leftovers.

2
00:00:18,051 --> 00:00:21,721
The best chefs in Korea
will turn your fridge inside out.

3
00:00:21,788 --> 00:00:23,923
The classy cooking show has returned.

4
00:00:23,990 --> 00:00:26,393
<i>-Chef & My Fridge!</i>
<i>-My Fridge!</i>

5
00:00:28,261 --> 00:00:29,262
Hello.

6
00:00:29,329 --> 00:00:30,196
WELCOME BACK

7
00:00:30,263 --> 00:00:31,765
Welcome to the show.

8
00:00:31,831 --> 00:00:36,436
Let's meet the guests who came
to let us rummage through their fridges.

9
00:00:36,503 --> 00:00:38,505
Today, we have

10
00:00:38,571 --> 00:00:41,908
two very lovely fairies

11
00:00:41,975 --> 00:00:44,110
-here on the show.
-Fairies?

12
00:00:44,177 --> 00:00:46,513
We present the fridge owners!

13
00:00:46,579 --> 00:00:47,747
Come on out!

14
00:00:47,814 --> 00:00:49,182
WE PRESENT THE FRIDGE OWNERS

15
00:00:49,816 --> 00:00:52,385
-Are they idol stars?
-Here are the fridge owners.

16
00:00:52,452 --> 00:00:54,521
Everyone, the fridge owners!

17
00:00:55,255 --> 00:00:57,457
Welcome to the show!

18
00:00:57,524 --> 00:00:59,559
-Thank you for coming.
-Hello.

19
00:00:59,626 --> 00:01:02,128
THE LOVELY FAIRIES SPECIAL
CHA JUN-HWAN & JUNG JAE-HYUNG

20
00:01:02,195 --> 00:01:04,631
THE FAIRY ON ICE, CHA JUN-HWAN

21
00:01:05,732 --> 00:01:07,167
Please look into the camera.

22
00:01:07,233 --> 00:01:08,535
LOOKING AROUND

23
00:01:08,601 --> 00:01:09,569
Yes, right.

24
00:01:10,370 --> 00:01:13,106
Hello, I'm Cha Jun-hwan,
a professional figure skater.

25
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:15,075
-Nice to meet you all.
-Welcome.

26
00:01:15,141 --> 00:01:18,078
-He's so good-looking.
-What?

27
00:01:18,144 --> 00:01:20,280
-Let me introduce the next guest.
-Sure.

28
00:01:20,346 --> 00:01:22,348
Welcome to <i>Fairy's Table</i>.

29
00:01:22,415 --> 00:01:23,750
-I made it look artistic.
-Right.

30
00:01:23,817 --> 00:01:25,118
It's good.

31
00:01:25,185 --> 00:01:26,453
Thank you for coming.

32
00:01:26,519 --> 00:01:27,387
It's really good.

33
00:01:27,454 --> 00:01:28,655
HE'S A GOOD COOK TOO

34
00:01:29,589 --> 00:01:32,258
A sentimental musician
who studied abroad in Paris,

35
00:01:32,325 --> 00:01:35,895
-Jung Jae-hyung, the music fairy.
-Please welcome Jae-hyung!

36
00:01:37,063 --> 00:01:39,265
-The music fairy.
-That's right.

37
00:01:39,332 --> 00:01:40,266
He's a fairy too.

38
00:01:40,333 --> 00:01:42,235
He's more like merry and silly.

39
00:01:42,302 --> 00:01:45,105
-Come on. Merry and silly?
-Is he serious?

40
00:01:45,171 --> 00:01:47,740
-Please don't be mad.
-One moment.

41
00:01:47,807 --> 00:01:49,809
Mr. Fairy, please don't be mad.

42
00:01:49,876 --> 00:01:53,012
-Were the guests of your show
-Yes?

43
00:01:53,079 --> 00:01:55,048
satisfied with your dishes?

44
00:01:55,115 --> 00:01:59,385
There's really no occasion
where one person cooks for hours for them.

45
00:01:59,452 --> 00:02:02,956
Maybe that's why,
but they all seem to like it.

46
00:02:03,022 --> 00:02:04,257
Your show needs to be grateful.

47
00:02:04,324 --> 00:02:06,493
The fact that these chefs
agreed to cook in 20 minutes--

48
00:02:06,559 --> 00:02:08,695
-Fifteen minutes. Yes.
-Fifteen minutes?

49
00:02:08,761 --> 00:02:12,031
Who said it was 20 minutes?
Was that the information you had?

50
00:02:12,098 --> 00:02:13,399
They only get 15 minutes.

51
00:02:13,466 --> 00:02:15,435
-What 20 minutes?
-The production crew and everyone

52
00:02:15,502 --> 00:02:16,402
must be grateful.

53
00:02:16,469 --> 00:02:19,539
Not only is it the rule
to cook in just 20 minutes…

54
00:02:19,606 --> 00:02:22,041
-I told you, it's 15 minutes!
-It's 15 minutes.

55
00:02:22,108 --> 00:02:24,277
-I'm sorry.
-I told you he was merry and silly.

56
00:02:24,344 --> 00:02:28,348
-I told you that he wasn't a fairy.
-I get why you said that now.

57
00:02:28,414 --> 00:02:29,983
One of them is the ice fairy

58
00:02:30,049 --> 00:02:33,153
and the other one is the music fairy.

59
00:02:33,219 --> 00:02:36,756
Jun-hwan brought
great honor to our country.

60
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:40,226
He won the gold medal in
the Asian Winter Games Harbin 2025.

61
00:02:40,293 --> 00:02:44,364
The first gold in the Asian Winter Games.
Please give him a round of applause.

62
00:02:44,430 --> 00:02:46,432
CONGRATULATIONS
ON THE GOLD MEDAL

63
00:02:46,499 --> 00:02:49,302
It was the first Asian Winter Games
held in eight years,

64
00:02:49,369 --> 00:02:51,938
as well as my first Asian Games,

65
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:53,506
so I was very excited.

66
00:02:53,573 --> 00:02:57,710
I'm glad I made the best of it
in the process of the game

67
00:02:57,777 --> 00:03:00,680
-and the result.
-You were amazing.

68
00:03:00,747 --> 00:03:04,851
He showed an amazing growth
in just four years.

69
00:03:04,918 --> 00:03:07,287
When you recorded fifth place
in the Beijing 2022 Winter Olympics,

70
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:10,924
the silver medalist
was Kagiyama from Japan.

71
00:03:10,990 --> 00:03:14,093
-You took out the silver medalist
-Right.

72
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:16,796
in the 2025 Asian Winter Games.

73
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:19,165
Yes, you won against him.

74
00:03:19,232 --> 00:03:20,433
This isn't a gang. "Took out"?

75
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:22,368
-He took him out.
-He did, though.

76
00:03:22,435 --> 00:03:25,338
-That's one evil hand gesture.
-I know.

77
00:03:25,405 --> 00:03:27,307
I was just that proud of him.

78
00:03:27,373 --> 00:03:31,911
Were you relieved after that first jump?
When did you know?

79
00:03:31,978 --> 00:03:33,780
-That's a good question.
-Me?

80
00:03:33,846 --> 00:03:36,482
I had to do my best in every single part.

81
00:03:36,549 --> 00:03:39,586
Don't you usually ruin other jumps
if the first one doesn't go well?

82
00:03:40,153 --> 00:03:43,656
-I'm sorry. This isn't your YouTube.
-Hey, Jae-hyung.

83
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:45,325
-Don't you want to know?
-He's running the show.

84
00:03:45,391 --> 00:03:46,960
-We'll ask him.
-We're here to do that.

85
00:03:47,026 --> 00:03:48,361
-Did you have that question?
-We'll do it.

86
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:52,131
-We do. We had all these questions.
-This isn't Fairy Jae-hyung.

87
00:03:52,198 --> 00:03:55,435
-I'm sorry.
-This is a warning, Jae-hyung.

88
00:03:55,501 --> 00:03:59,872
I hear <i>Chef & My Fridge </i>gave him
the inspiration to win the gold medal.

89
00:03:59,939 --> 00:04:02,075
-What?
-What is this? I was surprised too.

90
00:04:02,141 --> 00:04:05,011
I watch a lot of YouTube videos
on the day of my competition.

91
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:07,647
I have a lot of time until the game
after my morning practice.

92
00:04:07,714 --> 00:04:11,985
Also, it's too nerve-racking
to stay completely focused the whole time,

93
00:04:12,051 --> 00:04:15,622
so I watched lots of videos of this show
from both season one and two.

94
00:04:15,688 --> 00:04:19,292
-The 15-minute cook-offs were so exciting,
-Right.

95
00:04:19,359 --> 00:04:22,428
-and they gave me a dopamine rush.
-Right.

96
00:04:22,495 --> 00:04:25,765
-Like a sporting event.
-Yes, we're like a sporting event.

97
00:04:25,832 --> 00:04:28,568
And we were there yapping
throughout the cook-offs.

98
00:04:28,635 --> 00:04:30,503
The highlight is the five-minute check.

99
00:04:30,570 --> 00:04:32,772
When we go out at the five-minute mark?

100
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:35,708
We all took a part
in his achievement then.

101
00:04:35,775 --> 00:04:38,444
Then can we go somewhere
and say we took part in your gold…

102
00:04:38,511 --> 00:04:40,446
I'm sorry, but can you do it quietly?

103
00:04:41,881 --> 00:04:43,316
We're talking about
something important here!

104
00:04:43,383 --> 00:04:46,719
You could've done it below the table.
That was so loud.

105
00:04:46,786 --> 00:04:48,154
It's not a crime. Why would I do that?

106
00:04:48,221 --> 00:04:49,522
Think of the audio.

107
00:04:49,589 --> 00:04:52,492
Okay, I'm sorry!
I didn't know it'd be that loud.

108
00:04:52,558 --> 00:04:54,327
Why did you shake it, then?

109
00:04:54,394 --> 00:04:56,596
I was saying he won a gold
thanks to <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

110
00:04:56,896 --> 00:04:58,364
TAKING IT SMOOTHLY

111
00:04:58,698 --> 00:05:01,634
ROK TEASES HIM(?) QUIETLY
BY OPENING ONE BELOW THE TABLE

112
00:05:01,701 --> 00:05:03,303
Can we say that you are where you are
because of us?

113
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:05,438
It's just a bit of an exaggeration.

114
00:05:05,505 --> 00:05:08,074
Can we say Cha Jun-hwan is where he is
because of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>?

115
00:05:12,245 --> 00:05:13,913
THE FAIRY'S HUMOR

116
00:05:13,980 --> 00:05:16,215
-I guess that's a no.
-That's a bit of a stretch.

117
00:05:16,783 --> 00:05:18,484
All right. Thank you.

118
00:05:18,551 --> 00:05:22,455
He won in the Asian Games, so next is the
Milano Cortina 2026 Winter Games.

119
00:05:22,522 --> 00:05:23,489
Indeed.

120
00:05:23,556 --> 00:05:25,692
-I'm already anxious.
-Right?

121
00:05:25,758 --> 00:05:30,296
-Have you watched him compete?
-I have.

122
00:05:30,363 --> 00:05:32,865
I waited and watched him in real-time
in the Asian Games.

123
00:05:32,932 --> 00:05:35,835
I had very high expectations,

124
00:05:35,902 --> 00:05:38,004
and it was so beautiful
that it almost made me cry.

125
00:05:38,071 --> 00:05:40,573
He jumped like he had wings.

126
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:44,010
He'd get points deducted
if the jump was irrelevant to the music.

127
00:05:44,077 --> 00:05:46,446
Female skaters would do three spins,

128
00:05:46,512 --> 00:05:47,814
-truffle…
-"Truffle"?

129
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:50,750
-"Truffle"?
-Truffles are a type of mushroom.

130
00:05:50,817 --> 00:05:52,819
-That's a mushroom.
-A mushroom.

131
00:05:52,885 --> 00:05:55,922
That was my job kicking in.
The show got me thinking of truffles.

132
00:05:55,988 --> 00:05:58,057
-It must be very fragrant.
-Right.

133
00:05:58,124 --> 00:06:00,960
He'll tread smoothly like he's on oil.

134
00:06:01,027 --> 00:06:02,929
-Precisely.
-Across the ice.

135
00:06:02,995 --> 00:06:07,200
Now, we're going to take a look inside
Jun-hwan's fridge.

136
00:06:07,266 --> 00:06:11,437
Figure skating requires you
to stay on a strict diet, right?

137
00:06:11,504 --> 00:06:14,307
-Yes, it's better to stay lighter
-Right.

138
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:16,142
because we have to jump and spin.

139
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:20,079
It's a sporting event that requires you
to stay on a strict diet.

140
00:06:20,146 --> 00:06:22,382
<i>Chef & My Fridge </i>is the first show

141
00:06:22,448 --> 00:06:26,352
to find out Jun-hwan's diet,
the gold medalist's diet.

142
00:06:26,419 --> 00:06:29,822
-Let's take a look at the pictures.
-I'm curious.

143
00:06:29,889 --> 00:06:32,258
This is what he eats when he trains.

144
00:06:32,325 --> 00:06:34,026
-What is this?
-That's…

145
00:06:34,093 --> 00:06:35,328
-For breakfast,
-What's that?

146
00:06:35,395 --> 00:06:38,331
-I eat six pieces of meat.
-That one?

147
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:42,802
That's it, but it's not that much.
I eat less than half of that.

148
00:06:42,869 --> 00:06:44,570
-That's all you eat?
-So like three pieces?

149
00:06:44,637 --> 00:06:47,407
-I cut it up into six pieces.
-It's cut into six pieces.

150
00:06:47,473 --> 00:06:50,476
And the two on the top are what I eat
for lunch when I'm training.

151
00:06:50,543 --> 00:06:53,112
-Salad and fruit for lunch?
-No way.

152
00:06:53,179 --> 00:06:57,483
I usually only eat meat
for breakfast and lunch.

153
00:06:57,550 --> 00:06:59,886
Then when do you eat carbs?

154
00:06:59,952 --> 00:07:02,922
I eat some
when I feel physically strained.

155
00:07:02,989 --> 00:07:06,959
I live with my family, so for dinner,

156
00:07:07,026 --> 00:07:09,162
I'd share rice with my mom.

157
00:07:09,228 --> 00:07:12,832
We either share a bowl of instant rice
or not eat it at all.

158
00:07:12,899 --> 00:07:16,102
I usually stay away from carbs.

159
00:07:16,169 --> 00:07:19,338
-There's only about a spoonful.
-Only one meal includes carbs.

160
00:07:19,405 --> 00:07:22,341
And he eats only half a boiled egg.

161
00:07:22,408 --> 00:07:24,343
And look, he only eats one squid ear.

162
00:07:25,311 --> 00:07:28,614
-Squids don't have ears.
-It looks like an ear.

163
00:07:28,681 --> 00:07:30,483
-It's just an ear.
-The legs are better.

164
00:07:30,550 --> 00:07:32,518
Why do you only eat the squid ear?

165
00:07:32,585 --> 00:07:34,086
Is there a reason?

166
00:07:34,153 --> 00:07:37,323
-Why not the trunk or legs?
-Does it make him more flexible?

167
00:07:37,390 --> 00:07:40,193
-That could be it. It flutters.
-Yes, that part flutters.

168
00:07:40,259 --> 00:07:41,661
-Some people have them as pets.
-Yes.

169
00:07:41,727 --> 00:07:45,031
I think it's a coincidence,
but I don't pick and choose.

170
00:07:45,097 --> 00:07:46,699
Please don't misunderstand.

171
00:07:46,766 --> 00:07:48,601
He doesn't only eat the ears.

172
00:07:49,168 --> 00:07:51,170
I EAT EVERYTHING

173
00:07:51,237 --> 00:07:54,140
Do you need the chefs
to stick to your strict diet?

174
00:07:54,207 --> 00:07:57,176
Well, I'm here on my favorite show,

175
00:07:57,243 --> 00:08:00,213
-Right?
-and the chefs are here.

176
00:08:00,279 --> 00:08:03,049
I'll let myself go today.

177
00:08:03,115 --> 00:08:04,417
It's a special occasion. Amazing.

178
00:08:04,484 --> 00:08:09,021
All right. Let's find out what ingredients
Jun-hwan has in his fridge.

179
00:08:09,088 --> 00:08:13,392
Let us present the fridge
of the gold medalist figure skater

180
00:08:13,459 --> 00:08:17,063
of the Asian Winter Games Harbin 2025,
Cha Jun-hwan. Here it is!

181
00:08:17,697 --> 00:08:19,899
WHOA

182
00:08:19,966 --> 00:08:21,167
Here it is!

183
00:08:23,169 --> 00:08:25,638
You have more ingredients than I expected.

184
00:08:25,705 --> 00:08:28,574
THE FRIDGE HE USES WITH
HIS FAMILY IS FILLED TO THE BRIM

185
00:08:28,641 --> 00:08:32,712
I think these are mushroom soup.

186
00:08:32,778 --> 00:08:35,715
I work out in a cold environment,
so I like hot food.

187
00:08:35,781 --> 00:08:38,851
-I eat that with my lunch.
-I see.

188
00:08:38,918 --> 00:08:40,419
What about in the summer?

189
00:08:40,486 --> 00:08:43,422
-It's cold even in the summer.
-It is?

190
00:08:43,489 --> 00:08:47,560
The ice rink is cold all year round.
Come on.

191
00:08:47,627 --> 00:08:51,397
-It's cold there 365 days a year.
-Yes, right.

192
00:08:51,464 --> 00:08:53,366
I thought it'd be like
40 degrees in the summer.

193
00:08:54,433 --> 00:08:56,035
He'd have to swim there then.

194
00:08:56,836 --> 00:08:58,771
-Come on.
-All right.

195
00:08:58,838 --> 00:09:00,907
-This soup is a Western-style soup.
-Right.

196
00:09:00,973 --> 00:09:02,375
Do you like Western cuisine?

197
00:09:02,441 --> 00:09:04,110
I like both pasta and pizza.

198
00:09:04,176 --> 00:09:06,145
Both pasta and pizza.
You aren't a picky eater, then.

199
00:09:06,212 --> 00:09:10,316
Then do you eat pasta with light sauces?
Nothing too strong like tomato sauce?

200
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:13,586
-I just eat whatever I feel like.
-Okay, you aren't picky.

201
00:09:13,653 --> 00:09:15,254
-Pasta. Look over here.
-Hey, wait.

202
00:09:15,321 --> 00:09:17,623
-I found penne.
-Penne.

203
00:09:17,690 --> 00:09:20,426
-This is…
-I want to say something.

204
00:09:20,493 --> 00:09:24,330
-I eat a bit of it in the summer.
-How is tomato sauce considered strong?

205
00:09:24,397 --> 00:09:26,532
-That's when…
-Isn't that weird?

206
00:09:26,599 --> 00:09:28,034
I'm sorry. Did you hear that?

207
00:09:28,100 --> 00:09:30,770
This isn't your YouTube channel.

208
00:09:30,836 --> 00:09:33,205
If you want to film for your channel,
you can do that outside.

209
00:09:33,272 --> 00:09:36,242
Turn on your camera and do it alone.

210
00:09:36,309 --> 00:09:38,411
You're here at JTBC.

211
00:09:39,111 --> 00:09:40,780
He's overlapping with our audio.

212
00:09:40,846 --> 00:09:44,617
My mom packs some
for my lunch in the summer.

213
00:09:44,684 --> 00:09:49,355
She stir-fries
about ten pieces in perilla oil.

214
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:51,891
-Penne in perilla oil?
-Ten pieces?

215
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:53,526
-You only eat ten pieces?
-Ten pieces?

216
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:54,694
That's too little.

217
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:56,362
Can you pull out ten pieces?

218
00:09:56,429 --> 00:10:01,067
-Are you coaching me for the show?
-To see how much it is?

219
00:10:01,133 --> 00:10:02,301
I want to know the portion, that's all.

220
00:10:02,368 --> 00:10:05,171
-Come on.
-You can leave them out here.

221
00:10:05,237 --> 00:10:08,107
Let's see how big the portion is
with ten pieces.

222
00:10:08,174 --> 00:10:09,675
-He's making me tired.
-You must be curious.

223
00:10:09,742 --> 00:10:12,612
-They do become a bit bigger.
-Four pieces.

224
00:10:12,678 --> 00:10:13,946
Ten pieces aren't enough.

225
00:10:14,013 --> 00:10:17,350
We usually spear two to three pieces
of penne at a time.

226
00:10:17,416 --> 00:10:20,052
-That means he only gets three bites.
-Oh, that's eleven.

227
00:10:20,119 --> 00:10:22,455
That's all he eats.

228
00:10:22,521 --> 00:10:24,991
-How can you jump after just this?
-Right?

229
00:10:25,057 --> 00:10:26,058
That's why he's amazing.

230
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:28,427
Aren't the hosts amazing
for showing this right away?

231
00:10:29,528 --> 00:10:31,297
It's funny that you did as he told you.

232
00:10:32,598 --> 00:10:35,167
I think Jae-hyung made the right call
on this one.

233
00:10:35,234 --> 00:10:38,037
-This is all he eats.
-That's way too little.

234
00:10:38,104 --> 00:10:41,173
Why don't we make lots of food for him,
even if he doesn't finish?

235
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:43,843
-Let's do that to make him feel great.
-Thank you.

236
00:10:43,909 --> 00:10:46,345
Everyone, I found beef in plastic bags.

237
00:10:46,412 --> 00:10:49,248
There are four lumps
in separate plastic bags.

238
00:10:49,315 --> 00:10:52,218
That's probably
the portion I eat for breakfast.

239
00:10:52,284 --> 00:10:54,654
-Just one?
-One of these?

240
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,355
How many grams is this?

241
00:10:56,422 --> 00:10:59,992
Take a look. He won't even need
to go to the bathroom after eating this.

242
00:11:00,059 --> 00:11:02,895
-There's nothing to process.
-He hasn't eaten anything.

243
00:11:02,962 --> 00:11:04,330
This is about 20 g.

244
00:11:04,397 --> 00:11:07,667
-And he cuts it up into six pieces.
-I can have it as a snack right now.

245
00:11:07,733 --> 00:11:10,002
If I give my cat this little lump,

246
00:11:10,069 --> 00:11:11,904
-it'll refuse to eat it.
-Really?

247
00:11:11,971 --> 00:11:15,241
-Even cats will refuse to eat this.
-Yes, if I gave this to the cat.

248
00:11:15,307 --> 00:11:17,610
-Even dogs will refuse.
-They'll demand more.

249
00:11:17,677 --> 00:11:19,478
He ate this little and won a gold medal.

250
00:11:19,545 --> 00:11:21,147
He deserves another big round of applause.

251
00:11:21,213 --> 00:11:24,817
-My gosh.
-It's just amazing.

252
00:11:24,884 --> 00:11:27,586
-This is… Green plums.
-Pickled green plums.

253
00:11:27,653 --> 00:11:29,155
I love those,

254
00:11:29,221 --> 00:11:31,557
so I take them when I compete.

255
00:11:31,624 --> 00:11:34,126
I like fresh flavors and crunchy texture.

256
00:11:34,193 --> 00:11:35,828
Something crunchy and refreshing.

257
00:11:35,895 --> 00:11:37,129
I see some vegetables.

258
00:11:37,196 --> 00:11:40,733
Asparagus, carrot, enoki,

259
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,469
cucumber, potato, and water parsley.

260
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:44,970
Are there any vegetables you don't like?

261
00:11:45,037 --> 00:11:48,908
-I like everything, especially cabbage.
-Cabbage.

262
00:11:48,974 --> 00:11:53,212
-He's right. There's one head right here.
-He had one head here.

263
00:11:53,279 --> 00:11:56,382
And his mother has already
cut up a portion for him.

264
00:11:56,449 --> 00:11:59,418
-There they are. The main ingredient.
-The meat's there.

265
00:11:59,485 --> 00:12:00,619
Prime ribs.

266
00:12:00,686 --> 00:12:02,188
Beef brisket.

267
00:12:02,254 --> 00:12:03,489
These are from Hoengseong.

268
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:06,058
-What's this?
-These are beef rib bones, right?

269
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:09,161
-Yes, right. Beef rib bones.
-Beef rib bones.

270
00:12:09,228 --> 00:12:11,230
When I return home
after competing overseas,

271
00:12:11,297 --> 00:12:14,633
she'd always make
braised short ribs with those.

272
00:12:14,700 --> 00:12:17,036
That's actually my soul food.

273
00:12:17,103 --> 00:12:20,406
I'd eat it right out of the pot.
It's one of my favorites.

274
00:12:20,473 --> 00:12:24,243
Is there anything else you eat
when you come back from competing?

275
00:12:24,310 --> 00:12:26,579
Something you eat to treat yourself.

276
00:12:26,645 --> 00:12:28,714
I once went to Shanghai to compete,

277
00:12:28,781 --> 00:12:30,816
and they're famous for hot pot, right?

278
00:12:30,883 --> 00:12:32,785
I went to Haidilao Hot Pot,
and it was delicious.

279
00:12:33,385 --> 00:12:34,687
Isn't it very strong?

280
00:12:34,754 --> 00:12:35,955
-It's spicy.
-I had the tomato soup.

281
00:12:36,021 --> 00:12:37,456
He's not good with spicy food.

282
00:12:37,523 --> 00:12:39,091
He likes his food with a subtle flavor.

283
00:12:39,158 --> 00:12:41,193
-For the most part, yes.
-Got it.

284
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:43,262
I see some seafood here too.

285
00:12:43,329 --> 00:12:45,998
-Look. Abalone.
-Abalone. Do you like abalone?

286
00:12:46,065 --> 00:12:47,933
I love seafood.

287
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:51,170
-He loves abalone.
-I see you like seafood.

288
00:12:51,237 --> 00:12:52,371
Shrimp.

289
00:12:52,438 --> 00:12:53,773
-Squid ears!
-Squid ears.

290
00:12:53,839 --> 00:12:56,809
-This is what we meant by ears.
-This part.

291
00:12:56,876 --> 00:12:59,512
-The ears.
-That photo was a piece of these.

292
00:12:59,578 --> 00:13:01,947
His parents will eat the rest.

293
00:13:03,415 --> 00:13:05,985
People who love the ears
will only eat the ears.

294
00:13:06,051 --> 00:13:07,419
-The texture is different.
-Yeah.

295
00:13:07,486 --> 00:13:09,221
It has a certain texture.

296
00:13:09,288 --> 00:13:10,956
So he likes squid too.

297
00:13:11,023 --> 00:13:12,958
Let's move on
to his room temperature ingredients.

298
00:13:13,025 --> 00:13:14,794
-His instant rice!
-Instant rice.

299
00:13:14,860 --> 00:13:17,630
The instant rice he splits with his mom.

300
00:13:17,696 --> 00:13:19,098
-Yes.
-Right?

301
00:13:19,165 --> 00:13:22,701
It's the smaller portion.
It's not the big one.

302
00:13:22,768 --> 00:13:24,770
You're right. You split this with her?

303
00:13:24,837 --> 00:13:28,207
Yes, but I don't usually eat rice.

304
00:13:28,274 --> 00:13:30,943
Do you hold yourself back
even though you like it?

305
00:13:31,010 --> 00:13:34,847
I like all kinds of food,
but I have to be on a strict diet.

306
00:13:34,914 --> 00:13:36,048
That's what I usually do.

307
00:13:36,115 --> 00:13:39,451
That was all for Jun-hwan's fridge.

308
00:13:39,518 --> 00:13:42,021
WE HOPE YOU HAVE
A FILLING MEAL TODAY!

309
00:13:42,087 --> 00:13:46,025
Now, let's find out his orders

310
00:13:46,091 --> 00:13:49,461
and which chefs will cook
to fill the orders.

311
00:13:49,528 --> 00:13:52,198
Here are his orders.

312
00:13:52,565 --> 00:13:53,666
WHAT'S THE FIRST ORDER?

313
00:13:53,732 --> 00:13:56,602
What are his orders? The first order!

314
00:13:56,669 --> 00:13:59,572
"Milano Cortina Olympics, cheer up, baby."

315
00:14:01,941 --> 00:14:03,342
<i>Stay a bit stronger</i>

316
00:14:03,409 --> 00:14:04,510
What was that?

317
00:14:04,577 --> 00:14:05,878
-Right?
-What was that?

318
00:14:05,945 --> 00:14:09,748
-He sings with such an odd voice.
-"CHEER UP" by TWICE.

319
00:14:09,815 --> 00:14:12,184
You're already thinking about
the Milano Cortina 2026 Winter Games.

320
00:14:12,251 --> 00:14:16,422
-Yes, it's only a year from now,
-Right.

321
00:14:16,488 --> 00:14:18,390
and I'm here on the show before that.

322
00:14:18,457 --> 00:14:23,629
So I wanted to ask you to make something
that can give me energy to prepare for it.

323
00:14:23,696 --> 00:14:27,666
It doesn't have to be Italian
because it's the Milano Cortina Olympics.

324
00:14:27,733 --> 00:14:32,037
It can be in any kind of cuisine,
whatever the chefs can make for me.

325
00:14:32,104 --> 00:14:34,974
-Is it the Milan Matfia's turn?
-Something to cheer you up.

326
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:36,942
Let's find out the next order.

327
00:14:38,043 --> 00:14:40,279
-"Cheat dish for the crazy."
-"Cheat dish for the crazy."

328
00:14:40,346 --> 00:14:43,048
What does that mean?

329
00:14:43,115 --> 00:14:44,783
The pre-program song I used

330
00:14:44,850 --> 00:14:47,486
in the Asian Winter Games Harbin 2025
was called "Ballad for the Crazy."

331
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:50,589
-I see. "Ballad for the Crazy."
-It was so good.

332
00:14:50,656 --> 00:14:55,828
Today's my cheat day,
so I incorporated that in my order.

333
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:58,497
You want to eat like crazy today.

334
00:14:58,564 --> 00:15:00,366
I'll go.

335
00:15:00,432 --> 00:15:03,969
-My nickname is Crazy Chef.
-You're right!

336
00:15:04,036 --> 00:15:07,206
I'm a crazy chef,
so I'll make a cheat dish for the crazy.

337
00:15:07,273 --> 00:15:08,807
-Okay, then.
-Yes?

338
00:15:08,874 --> 00:15:10,476
My nickname is also…

339
00:15:11,610 --> 00:15:13,112
-Crazy.
-Crazy.

340
00:15:13,178 --> 00:15:14,680
He's seriously crazy.

341
00:15:14,747 --> 00:15:16,949
Aren't you just crazy, period?

342
00:15:17,016 --> 00:15:19,485
-Hyun-suk lost once last time.
-He did

343
00:15:19,551 --> 00:15:21,854
-But I won.
-You did

344
00:15:21,921 --> 00:15:24,490
I think I should keep this going
and fight him.

345
00:15:24,556 --> 00:15:26,392
You want to beat him
in your winning streak?

346
00:15:26,458 --> 00:15:28,527
-That's right.
-You've won twice in a row.

347
00:15:28,594 --> 00:15:31,597
-Poong challenges Hyun-suk.
-This will be fun.

348
00:15:31,664 --> 00:15:33,165
I'll take "cheer up, baby."

349
00:15:33,732 --> 00:15:35,868
-Wait, already?
-Wait.

350
00:15:35,935 --> 00:15:38,971
-He just wants to dance and do this.
-This dance.

351
00:15:39,538 --> 00:15:41,974
HE ALREADY MASTERED(?)
"CHEER UP"

352
00:15:42,041 --> 00:15:46,078
I'll throw in the dance
and pull off both cooking and dancing.

353
00:15:46,145 --> 00:15:47,713
-He'll kill two birds with one stone.
-Indeed.

354
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:51,317
-I'll also take "cheer up, baby."
-Hey, Nam-no.

355
00:15:51,383 --> 00:15:54,520
Then let us begin the first round
between Ho-young and Nam-no!

356
00:15:55,087 --> 00:15:58,757
THE COOK-OFFS WITH
JUN-HWAN'S INGREDIENTS BEGIN

357
00:15:58,824 --> 00:16:03,195
This is the first round of the cook-off
with Jun-hwan's ingredients.

358
00:16:03,262 --> 00:16:04,296
Milano Cortina Olympics…

359
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:09,268
That's the order.

360
00:16:09,335 --> 00:16:11,904
The dancing fairy, Chef Ho-young,

361
00:16:11,971 --> 00:16:14,239
is up against the anxious fairy,

362
00:16:14,306 --> 00:16:16,742
-Chef Nam-no.
-"Anxious fairy"?

363
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:18,243
They kind of look similar,

364
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:21,246
-except for the hair color.
-They have the same figure too.

365
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:24,016
He looks like little Ho-young.

366
00:16:24,083 --> 00:16:26,085
Some even say

367
00:16:26,151 --> 00:16:29,588
the one who controls Nam-no and Sung-jun

368
00:16:29,655 --> 00:16:32,624
-is actually Ho-young.
-He pulls the wires.

369
00:16:32,691 --> 00:16:35,194
That Ho-young is the head
of the Anti-Good Vibes Alliance.

370
00:16:35,260 --> 00:16:38,664
Ho-young, do you also not like
someone who looks like Jong-won?

371
00:16:38,731 --> 00:16:40,032
I don't really care for it.

372
00:16:41,533 --> 00:16:43,035
That's a pass.

373
00:16:43,102 --> 00:16:45,270
We have a surprise announcement
before you two begin.

374
00:16:45,337 --> 00:16:48,407
This round comes with chances
to earn special extra points.

375
00:16:48,474 --> 00:16:50,909
It's the cheer up points.

376
00:16:50,976 --> 00:16:52,378
-Cheer up points?
-Yes, cheer up points.

377
00:16:52,444 --> 00:16:54,346
The points
aren't just for your completed dish.

378
00:16:54,413 --> 00:16:58,317
If Jun-hwan, the fridge owner,
gets excited while you cook,

379
00:16:58,384 --> 00:17:03,055
-he will grant the cheer up points.
-Like the program component score.

380
00:17:03,122 --> 00:17:05,624
The points range from zero to five.

381
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:09,828
While they cook,
he's going to say, "Five for Ho-young!"

382
00:17:11,430 --> 00:17:12,698
ANY KIND OF PERFORMANCE IS OK!

383
00:17:12,765 --> 00:17:14,600
That was the torch relay performance.

384
00:17:14,666 --> 00:17:17,703
-Five points.
-He just gave that five points.

385
00:17:17,770 --> 00:17:21,774
Every performance
may give you extra points.

386
00:17:21,840 --> 00:17:22,674
CHEF NAM-NO: OLIVE OIL, CORN,

387
00:17:22,741 --> 00:17:24,176
BRISKET, ABALONE SOY SAUCE,
CABBAGE, SQUID, BLUE CRAB SAUCE,

388
00:17:24,243 --> 00:17:25,511
POTATO, TOFU, SCALLOP,
PEA, WATER PARSLEY, SHRIMP

389
00:17:25,577 --> 00:17:28,647
Chef Nam-no, what's your dish?

390
00:17:28,714 --> 00:17:30,749
The dish I prepared is called…

391
00:17:30,816 --> 00:17:33,519
<i>Fighting Squid</i>

392
00:17:33,585 --> 00:17:36,655
-<i>Fighting Squid</i>
-Fighting Squid.

393
00:17:36,722 --> 00:17:39,058
Am I the fighting squid?

394
00:17:40,592 --> 00:17:42,961
DOES IT MEAN "GOOD LUCK, SQUID"?

395
00:17:43,028 --> 00:17:45,597
He snapped for the first time today.

396
00:17:45,664 --> 00:17:47,766
-It could be misunderstood.
-This isn't good.

397
00:17:47,833 --> 00:17:49,902
I think there's a big misunderstanding.

398
00:17:49,968 --> 00:17:52,671
It's a squid dish to bid you a good fight.

399
00:17:53,705 --> 00:17:55,207
A squid dish to bid him a good fight.

400
00:17:55,274 --> 00:17:58,143
A squid dish to bid a good fight,
not for a fighting squid.

401
00:17:58,210 --> 00:18:01,580
-It's not for the fighting squid.
-He's quite sensitive.

402
00:18:01,647 --> 00:18:04,850
I'm going to make squid sundae.

403
00:18:04,917 --> 00:18:07,086
-Squid sundae.
-Squid sundae.

404
00:18:07,152 --> 00:18:09,154
Mollusks are high in taurine,

405
00:18:09,221 --> 00:18:11,256
-so it's a great source of energy.
-I see.

406
00:18:11,957 --> 00:18:14,793
I'll make sundae for the squid…

407
00:18:14,860 --> 00:18:16,195
-"Sundae for squid"?
-"Sundae for squid"?

408
00:18:16,261 --> 00:18:17,463
-Wait.
-What?

409
00:18:17,529 --> 00:18:18,897
-Squid?
-What is he saying?

410
00:18:18,964 --> 00:18:20,866
Who are you calling a squid?

411
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:24,570
What do you mean, sundae for squid?

412
00:18:24,636 --> 00:18:26,071
You get five points deducted.

413
00:18:26,138 --> 00:18:29,441
-Who are you calling a squid?
-He lost five points.

414
00:18:29,508 --> 00:18:32,678
-How can you call Jun-hwan a squid?
-A squid?

415
00:18:32,744 --> 00:18:34,546
-Nam-no, what's with you?
-Come on.

416
00:18:34,613 --> 00:18:36,115
Then is this Jun-hwan sundae?

417
00:18:36,782 --> 00:18:38,784
-Is that what it is?
-He's a troublemaker.

418
00:18:38,851 --> 00:18:41,787
I'll make sundae with squid.

419
00:18:41,854 --> 00:18:43,789
"Sundae for squid."

420
00:18:43,856 --> 00:18:46,024
I'll also prepare a Milan-style dressing

421
00:18:46,091 --> 00:18:49,194
with a hint of Korea
by using the water parsley.

422
00:18:49,261 --> 00:18:50,896
Lastly, I have one last wild card.

423
00:18:50,963 --> 00:18:52,898
I'll make it with secret ingredients.

424
00:18:53,465 --> 00:18:54,800
FULL OF ANTICIPATION

425
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:56,135
CHEF HO-YOUNG: ASPARAGUS,
GALBI SAUCE, MUSHROOM SOUP,

426
00:18:56,201 --> 00:18:57,402
TRUFFLE OIL, CORN,
ROASTED PEANUT, SESAME, SHRIMP,

427
00:18:57,469 --> 00:18:58,470
ZUCCHINI, STRIP LOIN,
CABBAGE, OYSTER SAUCE

428
00:18:58,537 --> 00:19:00,372
Chef Ho-young, what's your dish?

429
00:19:00,439 --> 00:19:02,841
The dish I prepared is called…

430
00:19:02,908 --> 00:19:03,909
Music, please.

431
00:19:05,377 --> 00:19:06,245
What?

432
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:07,546
WAIT, IS THIS…

433
00:19:07,613 --> 00:19:09,014
-What?
-What's he doing?

434
00:19:09,081 --> 00:19:11,216
PIKKI PIKKI

435
00:19:11,283 --> 00:19:13,452
THIS IS CALLED EXPERIENCE, KID

436
00:19:14,119 --> 00:19:15,587
SEXY

437
00:19:15,654 --> 00:19:17,890
Cab, Cab, Cabbage.

438
00:19:19,825 --> 00:19:20,959
PERFECT!

439
00:19:21,026 --> 00:19:22,761
-"Cab, Cab, Cabbage."
-"Cab, Cab, Cabbage."

440
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:24,496
You did the Pikki Pikki dance.

441
00:19:24,563 --> 00:19:27,699
He said he liked all vegetables,
but especially cabbage.

442
00:19:27,766 --> 00:19:31,103
-So I'll make a cabbage steak.
-Cabbage steak?

443
00:19:31,170 --> 00:19:33,005
Cabbage is gentle on the stomach,

444
00:19:33,071 --> 00:19:35,240
so it'll help you feel less nervous.

445
00:19:35,307 --> 00:19:38,877
You also need to eat protein,
so I'll cut up beef into small pieces,

446
00:19:38,944 --> 00:19:42,014
wrap it around with shrimp and asparagus,
then deep-fry it.

447
00:19:42,648 --> 00:19:45,117
Also, to show my support
for the Milano Cortina 2026 Winter Games,

448
00:19:45,184 --> 00:19:47,719
I'll make a gold medal
and serve it on the side.

449
00:19:48,520 --> 00:19:50,956
He's making the Olympic rings,
and he's making a gold medal.

450
00:19:51,023 --> 00:19:53,992
He's just telling him to participate,
but I'm rooting for your gold medal.

451
00:19:54,426 --> 00:19:55,527
A PERFECT INTENTION
FOLLOWED BY A PERFECT DANCE

452
00:19:55,594 --> 00:19:56,995
That's hard to beat.

453
00:19:57,663 --> 00:20:00,032
How many points do you want to give
after hearing about his dish?

454
00:20:00,098 --> 00:20:02,534
I think he deserves all these.

455
00:20:03,936 --> 00:20:05,404
-I see.
-Fifteen points.

456
00:20:05,470 --> 00:20:07,239
-Fifteen points.
-Nam-no is falling behind.

457
00:20:07,306 --> 00:20:11,243
Ho-young takes the lead
in the cheer up points.

458
00:20:11,310 --> 00:20:15,380
Now, starting with
"Milano Cortina Olympics, cheer up, baby."

459
00:20:15,447 --> 00:20:17,583
Let us begin the cook-off.

460
00:20:17,649 --> 00:20:19,851
He's an experienced chef and dancer.

461
00:20:19,918 --> 00:20:22,487
The man who's here to subdue Nam-no,

462
00:20:22,554 --> 00:20:25,457
a veteran member of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,
Chef Jung Ho-young.

463
00:20:25,524 --> 00:20:27,926
This man wants to beat Ho-young's record

464
00:20:27,993 --> 00:20:30,028
in both cooking and dancing.

465
00:20:30,095 --> 00:20:33,832
The dark horse of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,
Chef Yoon Nam-no.

466
00:20:33,899 --> 00:20:36,301
The doppelgänger match
between the two chefs.

467
00:20:36,368 --> 00:20:40,772
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

468
00:20:41,773 --> 00:20:43,175
Begin!

469
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:45,477
AN UNEXPECTED DOPPELGÄNGER MATCH

470
00:20:45,544 --> 00:20:47,713
Can they really do this in 15 minutes?

471
00:20:47,779 --> 00:20:51,149
It's exactly 15 minutes.
You keep saying 20, but it's 15.

472
00:20:51,216 --> 00:20:53,719
Why? Are you here to nitpick over that?

473
00:20:53,785 --> 00:20:54,753
You kept saying it was 20 minutes.

474
00:20:54,820 --> 00:20:58,056
-Can't you make it 20?
-They only get 15 minutes.

475
00:20:58,123 --> 00:20:59,224
There's the squid.

476
00:20:59,291 --> 00:21:01,593
He got the squid for Fighting Squid.

477
00:21:02,094 --> 00:21:04,496
1. EMPTY OUT THE TRUNK BY
PULLING OUT THE LEGS AND INNARDS

478
00:21:05,063 --> 00:21:06,832
WASHING IT CLEAN

479
00:21:06,898 --> 00:21:10,702
There's a similar dish
to squid sundae in Italian cuisine.

480
00:21:10,769 --> 00:21:13,071
It's made by peeling the skin, right?

481
00:21:13,138 --> 00:21:15,907
-It is. But he didn't.
-But I don't think…

482
00:21:15,974 --> 00:21:19,711
-The skin is tough, and it gets stuck.
-It's tough.

483
00:21:19,778 --> 00:21:21,413
But it's nutritious.

484
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:23,782
-Taurine is in the skin.
-It's in the skin.

485
00:21:23,849 --> 00:21:25,651
It's to give him energy.

486
00:21:26,885 --> 00:21:28,320
Chef Nam-no, what's that?

487
00:21:28,387 --> 00:21:30,155
-Tofu.
-Tofu.

488
00:21:30,222 --> 00:21:32,424
-He's making the sundae filling.
-Oh, he's using tofu.

489
00:21:32,491 --> 00:21:34,026
It's the sundae filling.

490
00:21:34,092 --> 00:21:36,895
-Will that go into the squid?
-Shrimp.

491
00:21:36,962 --> 00:21:39,965
He's adding shrimp and tofu.
That looks good.

492
00:21:40,532 --> 00:21:42,601
HO-YOUNG BEGINS WITH THE CABBAGE

493
00:21:43,302 --> 00:21:46,605
You put those sticks inside
to keep it intact, right?

494
00:21:46,672 --> 00:21:47,973
You're right.

495
00:21:48,240 --> 00:21:50,042
SALT PERFORMANCE

496
00:21:50,108 --> 00:21:51,376
There's his performance!

497
00:21:52,711 --> 00:21:55,681
Ho-young is putting on
a lot of performances today.

498
00:21:55,747 --> 00:21:57,015
CHEER UP POINT:
HO-YOUNG, 3 POINTS

499
00:21:57,582 --> 00:21:58,784
There's his performance!

500
00:22:00,419 --> 00:22:03,288
Ho-young is putting on
a lot of performances today.

501
00:22:03,355 --> 00:22:04,890
HIS HEAVY JUMP SUCCESSFULLY
GOT HIM CHEER UP POINTS

502
00:22:04,956 --> 00:22:08,160
There was a difference
in the height of the jump.

503
00:22:08,226 --> 00:22:10,162
He's cooking cabbage like it's steak.

504
00:22:11,430 --> 00:22:13,465
There's beef.

505
00:22:13,532 --> 00:22:16,968
Jun-hwan usually has
only one lump per meal.

506
00:22:17,035 --> 00:22:19,204
He's going to grind it.

507
00:22:19,271 --> 00:22:20,372
Will he grind it in a blender?

508
00:22:20,439 --> 00:22:21,740
Ho-young, which cut is it?

509
00:22:21,807 --> 00:22:23,909
-It's strip loin.
-Strip loin.

510
00:22:23,975 --> 00:22:26,144
-Strip loin.
-I see.

511
00:22:26,211 --> 00:22:30,282
Is it okay to use strip loin
instead of rump steak?

512
00:22:30,349 --> 00:22:33,318
That was a really technical question.

513
00:22:33,385 --> 00:22:36,388
-Why won't they answer me?
-Can someone else answer him?

514
00:22:36,455 --> 00:22:37,889
I didn't hear him.

515
00:22:37,956 --> 00:22:40,192
Can you use strip loin
to make ground beef?

516
00:22:40,258 --> 00:22:41,727
Yes, it's much more tender.

517
00:22:42,327 --> 00:22:44,763
SATISFIED

518
00:22:46,098 --> 00:22:47,366
What's that?

519
00:22:47,432 --> 00:22:49,634
-What's that?
-That's nice.

520
00:22:49,701 --> 00:22:51,169
Is that a tool for pounding meat?

521
00:22:51,236 --> 00:22:52,304
Isn't that a stapler?

522
00:22:53,638 --> 00:22:55,073
Are you using a stapler?

523
00:22:55,140 --> 00:22:57,476
People often use that
when making pork cutlet.

524
00:22:57,542 --> 00:22:59,878
-It's a meat tenderizer.
-It looks like a stapler.

525
00:22:59,945 --> 00:23:02,814
-Right. A stapler.
-A stapler.

526
00:23:02,881 --> 00:23:06,184
-It's Japanese cuisine.
-It is.

527
00:23:07,152 --> 00:23:08,387
Is he making hamburger steak?

528
00:23:08,453 --> 00:23:10,655
-Is he?
-It looks like hamburger steak.

529
00:23:11,156 --> 00:23:13,458
He's using beef too.

530
00:23:13,525 --> 00:23:14,960
It's brisket.

531
00:23:15,026 --> 00:23:17,028
Nam-no is using beef brisket.

532
00:23:17,095 --> 00:23:18,697
-Brisket.
-Oh, he's using brisket.

533
00:23:19,765 --> 00:23:20,966
Brisket versus strip loin.

534
00:23:21,032 --> 00:23:23,935
3. MIX BRISKET, SALT, ABALONE
SOY SAUCE, CRAB SAUCE,

535
00:23:24,002 --> 00:23:25,570
OLIVE OIL, AND WATER PARSLEY

536
00:23:25,637 --> 00:23:27,539
Chef Nam-no is making the squid filling.

537
00:23:27,606 --> 00:23:29,641
-Are you putting everything in?
-Yes.

538
00:23:29,708 --> 00:23:32,577
The pieces for the filling
are quite large.

539
00:23:33,211 --> 00:23:35,247
-What?
-The pieces are pretty big.

540
00:23:35,313 --> 00:23:37,783
-He has lots of questions.
-He does.

541
00:23:37,849 --> 00:23:40,519
It's a new way of attacking
from the guest.

542
00:23:40,585 --> 00:23:43,355
-It's fun to watch in real life.
-It really is.

543
00:23:43,655 --> 00:23:46,091
A FLOOD OF QUESTIONS
DRIVEN BY RISING DOPAMINE

544
00:23:46,158 --> 00:23:48,727
The ingredients for dumpling fillings
are usually finely chopped.

545
00:23:48,794 --> 00:23:52,464
But he probably didn't chop them as finely
to bring out the texture.

546
00:23:52,531 --> 00:23:53,398
He put in brisket too.

547
00:23:53,765 --> 00:23:56,334
SEALING THE SQUID OFF
WITH A WOODEN STICK

548
00:23:57,469 --> 00:23:59,738
He's using a toothpick.

549
00:23:59,805 --> 00:24:00,639
SNAP

550
00:24:01,606 --> 00:24:03,742
It's going to break.

551
00:24:04,443 --> 00:24:05,710
It's not working.

552
00:24:05,777 --> 00:24:07,379
Didn't it break? I heard it snap.

553
00:24:07,446 --> 00:24:08,513
No.

554
00:24:09,347 --> 00:24:10,682
TREMBLING

555
00:24:10,749 --> 00:24:12,884
This place is a bloodbath.

556
00:24:12,951 --> 00:24:16,488
Jun-hwan used to only eat squid ears.

557
00:24:16,555 --> 00:24:19,391
But it seems like
he'll get the whole trunk today.

558
00:24:19,991 --> 00:24:21,827
HO-YOUNG MAKES THE SAUCE

559
00:24:22,394 --> 00:24:25,464
4. BLEND ROASTED PEANUTS,
SESAME, MUSHROOM SOUP,

560
00:24:25,530 --> 00:24:27,032
OYSTER SAUCE, AND WATER

561
00:24:27,098 --> 00:24:28,533
-What's that?
-Did it turn out all right?

562
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:30,268
-Yes.
-It came out well.

563
00:24:30,335 --> 00:24:31,570
What's that?

564
00:24:31,636 --> 00:24:32,604
The sauce.

565
00:24:32,671 --> 00:24:34,206
Oh, you were making the sauce?

566
00:24:34,272 --> 00:24:36,908
This is the sauce for the deep-fry.

567
00:24:36,975 --> 00:24:40,011
-It's made with peanuts.
-I see.

568
00:24:40,078 --> 00:24:42,848
He's using potatoes.

569
00:24:42,914 --> 00:24:44,449
Are you making the Olympic rings?

570
00:24:44,516 --> 00:24:45,617
Yes.

571
00:24:45,684 --> 00:24:47,853
-Really?
-How is he going to do that?

572
00:24:47,919 --> 00:24:49,921
How will you make the Olympic rings?

573
00:24:50,622 --> 00:24:53,758
He's making a hole in the middle.

574
00:24:53,825 --> 00:24:55,994
You have nine minutes left.

575
00:24:56,061 --> 00:24:57,596
Only nine minutes?

576
00:24:57,929 --> 00:24:59,664
HO-YOUNG USES A ZUCCHINI

577
00:25:00,232 --> 00:25:02,534
HE ALSO MAKES A RING
WITH A ROUND COOKIE CUTTER

578
00:25:03,935 --> 00:25:05,504
What's that? He's using corn?

579
00:25:06,137 --> 00:25:06,972
Corn?

580
00:25:07,706 --> 00:25:11,409
-It'll become the gold medal.
-That's the gold medal.

581
00:25:11,476 --> 00:25:14,212
How will he turn that into a gold medal?

582
00:25:15,413 --> 00:25:17,916
THE DOPPELGÄNGERS
LIGHT THE STOVE AT THE SAME TIME

583
00:25:19,117 --> 00:25:20,352
Why won't it work?

584
00:25:21,553 --> 00:25:25,657
He's frying that right now.
He's pan-frying it.

585
00:25:25,724 --> 00:25:30,095
Did you make three pieces hoping he'd win
either gold, silver, or bronze medal?

586
00:25:30,161 --> 00:25:31,930
I'm hoping he'll win
three more gold medals.

587
00:25:31,997 --> 00:25:33,832
MAKING UP THE STORY(?)

588
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:37,536
He's calling those the gold medals,
but I'm not so sure.

589
00:25:37,602 --> 00:25:39,170
-The ribbon.
-That's the ribbon?

590
00:25:39,838 --> 00:25:41,306
-The ribbon? Right.
-The ribbon.

591
00:25:41,373 --> 00:25:43,808
I even made the ribbon with asparagus.

592
00:25:44,543 --> 00:25:47,812
HE FINALLY TURNED ON THE STOVE

593
00:25:48,780 --> 00:25:50,515
HUFFING AND PUFFING

594
00:25:51,983 --> 00:25:53,485
HE BREATHES HEAVILY AS HE
RESTS THE RINGS INTO THE PAN

595
00:25:53,552 --> 00:25:55,720
It's the Olympic rings.

596
00:25:55,787 --> 00:25:57,455
-Is that it?
-He's frying those.

597
00:25:58,423 --> 00:25:59,558
He's frying the potato.

598
00:25:59,624 --> 00:26:01,326
Will it stick together?

599
00:26:01,393 --> 00:26:04,095
-He used starch.
-Oh, I see.

600
00:26:04,162 --> 00:26:06,197
That looks pretty.

601
00:26:06,264 --> 00:26:08,533
I thought he'd add the colors,

602
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:11,469
-but I guess he didn't care to do that.
-They're all just white.

603
00:26:11,536 --> 00:26:14,372
-I thought that was a given.
-Of course.

604
00:26:14,439 --> 00:26:18,510
I thought he'd use carrot and zucchini
to give it color.

605
00:26:18,577 --> 00:26:20,612
The colors stand for something.

606
00:26:21,046 --> 00:26:22,581
STARING

607
00:26:22,647 --> 00:26:24,416
I think the cabbage is burning.

608
00:26:24,482 --> 00:26:26,451
-It's not. It's okay.
-Is it?

609
00:26:26,518 --> 00:26:29,788
-It's better when it's burnt.
-That's true.

610
00:26:29,988 --> 00:26:31,022
PEEKS

611
00:26:32,490 --> 00:26:35,694
-It's burnt!
-I told you it was burning!

612
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:38,029
-It's burnt!
-I told you it was burning!

613
00:26:38,096 --> 00:26:41,232
-Chef Ho-young, how did that happen?
-I told you it was burning!

614
00:26:41,299 --> 00:26:43,768
-Why did you put the lid on it?
-For us to stop staring at it.

615
00:26:43,835 --> 00:26:47,606
I have to grill it like this
to create the flavor I'm going for.

616
00:26:47,672 --> 00:26:50,642
Gosh, but it obviously looks burnt.

617
00:26:50,709 --> 00:26:52,978
-It's like burnt linoleum flooring.
-Indeed.

618
00:26:53,044 --> 00:26:55,313
-"Burnt linoleum flooring"?
-Just be honest.

619
00:26:55,380 --> 00:26:58,483
No, everything is going just as planned.

620
00:26:58,550 --> 00:27:01,152
-Is it really?
-That cabbage is your main dish.

621
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:02,988
NAM-NO USES CABBAGE TOO

622
00:27:03,555 --> 00:27:06,024
8. STIR-FRY CHOPPED CABBAGE,
CORN KERNELS,

623
00:27:06,091 --> 00:27:07,692
SALT, AND BLUE CRAB SAUCE

624
00:27:10,261 --> 00:27:11,896
You'll get additional points
for performances,

625
00:27:11,963 --> 00:27:14,132
-but both of you aren't doing much.
-Six minutes.

626
00:27:14,199 --> 00:27:15,967
The salt sprinkling was it.

627
00:27:16,034 --> 00:27:19,070
We aren't seeing many points
being given out.

628
00:27:19,137 --> 00:27:20,305
Is that a performance?

629
00:27:20,372 --> 00:27:22,107
IS THAT A PERFORMANCE?

630
00:27:22,173 --> 00:27:23,274
Wait.

631
00:27:26,411 --> 00:27:27,812
Why won't it get lit on fire?

632
00:27:28,813 --> 00:27:31,549
It won't get lit on fire!
He wanted to perform a flambé.

633
00:27:32,117 --> 00:27:33,652
It's supposed to catch fire.

634
00:27:33,718 --> 00:27:35,020
HO-YOUNG DIDN'T GET ANY POINTS

635
00:27:36,054 --> 00:27:38,423
What's Chef Nam-no doing?

636
00:27:38,490 --> 00:27:41,559
I'm stir-frying cabbage,
then I'll smoke it in my way.

637
00:27:41,626 --> 00:27:43,928
-Whoa.
-He'll stir-fry it, then smoke it.

638
00:27:44,496 --> 00:27:47,232
LEAVING THE CONFUSED
HO-YOUNG BEHIND

639
00:27:48,433 --> 00:27:50,802
CHOPSTICKS OVER FIRE?

640
00:27:50,869 --> 00:27:51,703
What's he doing?

641
00:27:52,904 --> 00:27:55,607
-What's that?
-He's going to smoke it.

642
00:27:55,674 --> 00:27:58,343
-Oh, my.
-He's putting on a fire show.

643
00:27:58,410 --> 00:27:59,978
Jun-hwan, any points?

644
00:28:00,045 --> 00:28:02,047
-It's the torch relay.
-The torch?

645
00:28:02,113 --> 00:28:05,350
-It's the torch relay.
-The torch? It's the torch relay.

646
00:28:05,417 --> 00:28:08,019
What? Hey, what is he doing?

647
00:28:08,086 --> 00:28:09,721
What does he get
for the torch performance?

648
00:28:09,788 --> 00:28:12,457
What's the score
for the torch performance?

649
00:28:12,524 --> 00:28:14,359
-Three points for Nam-no.
-How many points?

650
00:28:14,426 --> 00:28:15,627
-Three.
-Three points!

651
00:28:15,694 --> 00:28:17,462
-Three.
-Three points!

652
00:28:17,529 --> 00:28:18,963
HE GETS 3 POINTS
FOR THE TORCH TECHNIQUE

653
00:28:19,831 --> 00:28:23,435
He puts on a torch performance!

654
00:28:24,035 --> 00:28:26,404
My gosh. It's the Olympics.

655
00:28:27,605 --> 00:28:29,941
THE HIGHLIGHT: HE GRABS
THE CABBAGE OUT FROM THE SMOKE

656
00:28:30,008 --> 00:28:31,843
-Points?
-Three points.

657
00:28:31,910 --> 00:28:34,646
-Five points.
-It goes up to five points!

658
00:28:35,313 --> 00:28:36,314
Three points.

659
00:28:36,381 --> 00:28:39,951
It goes up to five points!

660
00:28:42,987 --> 00:28:44,823
That was amazing.

661
00:28:44,889 --> 00:28:48,226
Sung-ju, it's five minutes.
Please go out on the field now.

662
00:28:48,293 --> 00:28:49,627
My gosh.

663
00:28:49,694 --> 00:28:53,598
The torch is still going strong.
The fire is still lit up.

664
00:28:53,665 --> 00:28:55,200
You need to roll the hoop!

665
00:28:55,266 --> 00:28:59,771
You need to put on
a performance like this.

666
00:28:59,838 --> 00:29:02,307
I'm reminded of the 1988 Summer Olympics.

667
00:29:02,373 --> 00:29:04,209
The torch is still on fire.

668
00:29:04,776 --> 00:29:06,311
HO-YOUNG BEGINS TO DEEP-FRY

669
00:29:06,811 --> 00:29:09,814
7. MIX CHOPPED SHRIMP
AND ASPARAGUS WITH CORN KERNELS

670
00:29:10,381 --> 00:29:12,484
8. MIX FLOUR, WATER
AND VEGETABLES

671
00:29:12,550 --> 00:29:14,119
TO MAKE VEGETABLE BATTER

672
00:29:14,686 --> 00:29:16,821
HE COATS SEASONED STRIP LOIN
WITH FLOUR

673
00:29:17,388 --> 00:29:19,524
USING BOTH HANDS

674
00:29:20,125 --> 00:29:21,693
THE VEGETABLE BATTER WRAPS
THE STRIP LOIN

675
00:29:21,760 --> 00:29:24,262
-It's like arancini.
-He's using beef.

676
00:29:24,329 --> 00:29:26,264
It's like fried hamburger steak.

677
00:29:26,331 --> 00:29:27,966
IT GOES STRAIGHT INTO THE OIL

678
00:29:28,533 --> 00:29:29,534
NAM-NO MAKES THE DRESSING

679
00:29:29,601 --> 00:29:31,603
What's that? White balsamic vinegar?

680
00:29:32,170 --> 00:29:35,373
7. MIX WHITE BALSAMIC VINEGAR,
SALT, AND OLIVE OIL

681
00:29:35,440 --> 00:29:36,841
TO MAKE THE DRESSING

682
00:29:37,108 --> 00:29:39,844
HE CHECKS ON THE SQUID TOO

683
00:29:40,411 --> 00:29:41,946
THE SQUID SUNDAE IS
COOKED DELICIOUSLY

684
00:29:42,013 --> 00:29:43,414
It's cooked well.

685
00:29:43,481 --> 00:29:46,384
Are you serving the Olympic rings
without colors?

686
00:29:46,451 --> 00:29:48,186
-No, it's not colored.
-It's not colored.

687
00:29:48,253 --> 00:29:49,487
No colors.

688
00:29:49,554 --> 00:29:52,590
If I were you, I'd top it with condiments
like gochujang and soy sauce.

689
00:29:52,657 --> 00:29:53,992
That's a good idea.

690
00:29:54,058 --> 00:29:57,395
-Then he can give it colors.
-What a shame. Yes, he can do that.

691
00:29:57,462 --> 00:29:59,531
It really is a shame.

692
00:29:59,597 --> 00:30:03,635
Jun-hwan, how many points does he get
for serving these as plain whites?

693
00:30:03,701 --> 00:30:05,503
Everything is white. One point.

694
00:30:05,570 --> 00:30:07,639
Only one point.

695
00:30:07,705 --> 00:30:09,507
-Put some gochujang on it.
-Put gochujang on it.

696
00:30:09,574 --> 00:30:11,276
-I can't.
-Why not?

697
00:30:11,342 --> 00:30:14,245
Is there anything I can try?
What's this again?

698
00:30:14,312 --> 00:30:16,281
-Cabbage.
-Cabbage.

699
00:30:16,848 --> 00:30:18,616
-The smoked cabbage.
-Let me try Nam-no's cabbage.

700
00:30:18,683 --> 00:30:20,919
Let me try Nam-no's cabbage.

701
00:30:20,985 --> 00:30:23,021
You have 2 minutes and 42 seconds left.

702
00:30:23,087 --> 00:30:24,823
No way. Already?

703
00:30:24,889 --> 00:30:26,958
-So? What's it like?
-Gosh, time flew by.

704
00:30:27,025 --> 00:30:31,396
Does it taste like
it'll give him a gold medal?

705
00:30:31,462 --> 00:30:33,131
It fails to qualify!

706
00:30:33,198 --> 00:30:34,999
-Why?
-Why?

707
00:30:35,066 --> 00:30:36,668
It fails to qualify!

708
00:30:36,734 --> 00:30:38,169
LOLOL!

709
00:30:38,236 --> 00:30:39,804
-It's too bland.
-Is it?

710
00:30:39,871 --> 00:30:42,373
-It's not.
-It's too bland.

711
00:30:42,440 --> 00:30:44,008
Isn't it too bland?

712
00:30:44,075 --> 00:30:46,110
You need to add a little more salt.

713
00:30:46,177 --> 00:30:48,146
-It'll be served with sundae.
-Oh, I see.

714
00:30:48,213 --> 00:30:51,082
It'll be served with sundae?
Goodness gracious.

715
00:30:51,149 --> 00:30:53,718
-It needs a bit more salt.
-It'll go out like this. Is it okay?

716
00:30:54,319 --> 00:30:56,521
HO-YOUNG FLIPS THE CABBAGE

717
00:30:57,689 --> 00:31:01,593
This is how it should look.
That looks good.

718
00:31:02,293 --> 00:31:06,631
HE SERVES THE CABBAGE
WITH THE RIGHT SIDE(?) UP

719
00:31:06,698 --> 00:31:08,933
Is it okay? I think he's making the sauce.

720
00:31:10,168 --> 00:31:13,538
9. BOIL COOKING WINE, SUGAR,
SOY SAUCE, AND CRUSHED GARLIC

721
00:31:13,605 --> 00:31:15,006
TO MAKE THE SAUCE

722
00:31:15,073 --> 00:31:17,876
It'll go out like this. Is it okay?

723
00:31:17,942 --> 00:31:19,911
-It's okay. The burnt side is the bottom.
-Is it?

724
00:31:20,478 --> 00:31:22,947
IT'S OKAY(?) THE BURNT SIDE IS
FACING DOWN

725
00:31:23,014 --> 00:31:24,649
Okay. That's good, then.

726
00:31:25,383 --> 00:31:27,418
-Two minutes.
-One minute.

727
00:31:27,485 --> 00:31:29,087
Time flew by so quickly.

728
00:31:29,153 --> 00:31:31,155
-Is this the sauce?
-Yes.

729
00:31:31,222 --> 00:31:32,891
-The sauce.
-The sauce is important. Try some.

730
00:31:32,957 --> 00:31:35,860
Let me try Ho-young's sauce.
You have 1 minute and 35 seconds left.

731
00:31:37,495 --> 00:31:42,267
Is it a taste that'll help him
set the new world record?

732
00:31:43,234 --> 00:31:45,770
Not yet. This is a bit bland too.

733
00:31:46,337 --> 00:31:49,974
You made it too bland
because he said he liked subtle flavors.

734
00:31:50,041 --> 00:31:52,076
-What are you tossing in?
-Mushroom soup.

735
00:31:52,143 --> 00:31:54,045
-Mushroom soup?
-Mushroom soup goes in.

736
00:31:54,112 --> 00:31:56,915
Put in a little more salt. Trust me.

737
00:31:56,981 --> 00:31:59,784
-Just a little.
-And do a performance. That's it!

738
00:31:59,851 --> 00:32:01,486
And do a performance.

739
00:32:01,552 --> 00:32:05,189
HE THROWS IN LOTS OF SALT
TRYING TO PUT ON A PERFORMANCE

740
00:32:05,256 --> 00:32:07,458
-That was too much!
-Is that okay?

741
00:32:07,525 --> 00:32:09,460
-That's it. Yes.
-That was a lot.

742
00:32:09,527 --> 00:32:11,129
You don't have much time.

743
00:32:11,195 --> 00:32:13,431
-Let me try it again.
-I think it'll be too salty.

744
00:32:13,498 --> 00:32:14,933
It can't be. I'll be doomed.

745
00:32:16,167 --> 00:32:17,068
So?

746
00:32:18,403 --> 00:32:22,106
-It must be salty.
-It's salty! Oh, no!

747
00:32:22,173 --> 00:32:25,443
-It must be salty.
-It's salty! Oh, no!

748
00:32:25,510 --> 00:32:27,578
It's perfect for my taste!

749
00:32:28,246 --> 00:32:31,449
-It's much better than before.
-Really?

750
00:32:31,516 --> 00:32:33,551
Nam-no, you should finish up too

751
00:32:33,751 --> 00:32:37,188
8. SERVE SMOKED VEGETABLES
ON A PLATE AND POUR DRESSING

752
00:32:37,755 --> 00:32:40,792
CHECKING THE SQUID SUNDAE

753
00:32:41,626 --> 00:32:44,028
ANTI-GOOD VIBES

754
00:32:44,095 --> 00:32:45,496
Nam-no, you're almost out of time.

755
00:32:45,563 --> 00:32:47,665
-You have 33 seconds.
-You have 30 seconds!

756
00:32:47,732 --> 00:32:49,867
He's going to present it
with the gold medal.

757
00:32:49,934 --> 00:32:52,503
-And he adds the ribbon.
-Thirty seconds!

758
00:32:52,570 --> 00:32:55,373
-The sauce! Ho-young!
-You have 30 seconds

759
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:57,241
-The fritters.
-What about these?

760
00:32:57,308 --> 00:32:59,510
-The fritters.
-What about these?

761
00:32:59,577 --> 00:33:01,446
-I have to get them out.
-Get them out.

762
00:33:01,512 --> 00:33:04,115
-You have 20 seconds.
-Only 20 seconds!

763
00:33:04,182 --> 00:33:06,084
-The sundae is out!
-Twenty seconds!

764
00:33:06,150 --> 00:33:07,318
The sundae is out!

765
00:33:07,385 --> 00:33:10,388
I wonder how it'll look. He just cut it!

766
00:33:10,455 --> 00:33:12,123
It's too hot!

767
00:33:12,190 --> 00:33:14,092
You're out of time.
You have to do it even if it's hot.

768
00:33:14,158 --> 00:33:16,828
-Ten, nine, eight, seven…
-Nine, eight, seven…

769
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:21,666
HO-YOUNG TAKES OUT
THE STRIP LOIN FRITTERS

770
00:33:21,733 --> 00:33:24,602
-Eight, seven, six…
-Eight, seven, six…

771
00:33:25,169 --> 00:33:26,337
SCREAMING

772
00:33:26,604 --> 00:33:28,639
MAXIMUM DOPAMINE LEVEL

773
00:33:28,906 --> 00:33:30,742
THE OLYMPIC RINGS GO UP

774
00:33:31,175 --> 00:33:33,611
CUTTING THE STRIP LOIN FRITTERS

775
00:33:33,845 --> 00:33:35,613
FINISHES OFF WITH WATER PARSLEY

776
00:33:36,014 --> 00:33:37,982
FINISHES OFF
WITH STRIP LOIN FRITTERS

777
00:33:38,049 --> 00:33:41,252
-Two, one. It's over!
-The bell.

778
00:33:41,319 --> 00:33:44,422
Ring the bell! Yes, Nam-no is finished.

779
00:33:45,957 --> 00:33:47,925
He's done. Ho-yong is done too.

780
00:33:48,493 --> 00:33:50,328
…HOWEVER

781
00:33:50,828 --> 00:33:52,830
It's not fully cooked.

782
00:33:52,897 --> 00:33:54,032
-Exactly.
-Right.

783
00:33:54,098 --> 00:33:57,568
-It's still quite pink.
-No, it's supposed to be tender.

784
00:33:57,635 --> 00:34:00,004
Is it supposed to be tender? It's beef.

785
00:34:00,071 --> 00:34:02,006
They're both done.

786
00:34:02,573 --> 00:34:04,542
-The Olympic rings.
-It's there.

787
00:34:04,609 --> 00:34:06,277
Fifteen minutes.
I told you it was fifteen.

788
00:34:06,344 --> 00:34:08,079
My heart is beating so quickly.

789
00:34:08,146 --> 00:34:09,747
It's like commentating
on a sporting event.

790
00:34:09,814 --> 00:34:11,115
It's fifteen minutes.

791
00:34:11,182 --> 00:34:14,552
-It ended in a flash.
-Right. Fifteen minutes fly by.

792
00:34:14,619 --> 00:34:18,156
Both chefs have completed making
their dishes for Jun-hwan.

793
00:34:18,222 --> 00:34:19,624
What was it like to watch them?

794
00:34:19,690 --> 00:34:22,060
-It was so much fun.
-I'm glad.

795
00:34:22,126 --> 00:34:24,962
I only ever watched it
on my phone until today,

796
00:34:25,029 --> 00:34:27,465
but in real life, these 15 minutes

797
00:34:27,532 --> 00:34:29,801
were more nerve-racking than my own games.

798
00:34:29,867 --> 00:34:31,369
It went by so quickly.

799
00:34:31,436 --> 00:34:34,539
It felt like
it had only been five minutes.

800
00:34:34,605 --> 00:34:38,042
Please try Fighting Squid first.

801
00:34:38,109 --> 00:34:39,744
HEALTHY CABBAGE STIR-FRY

802
00:34:40,411 --> 00:34:44,148
TOPPED WITH SQUID SUNDAE
TO GIVE HIM ENERGY

803
00:34:44,949 --> 00:34:49,120
CHEF YOON NAM-NO'S
FIGHTING SQUID

804
00:34:49,754 --> 00:34:51,756
Gosh, the Olympic rings stand out.

805
00:34:51,823 --> 00:34:54,892
-I see, even though it's not colored.
-That's right.

806
00:34:54,959 --> 00:34:57,061
Nam-no looks nervous.

807
00:34:57,128 --> 00:34:58,496
How should he eat this?

808
00:34:58,563 --> 00:35:01,399
Try the cabbage stir-fry first.
It's a good appetizer.

809
00:35:01,466 --> 00:35:04,669
He eats vegetables often,
so he probably knows when it tastes good.

810
00:35:04,735 --> 00:35:06,737
I wonder if it's made to his taste.

811
00:35:06,804 --> 00:35:09,373
He must be hungry
after his morning training.

812
00:35:09,440 --> 00:35:11,776
He's very strict
about managing his condition.

813
00:35:11,843 --> 00:35:12,844
How is it?

814
00:35:14,178 --> 00:35:16,047
EYES WIDENED

815
00:35:16,114 --> 00:35:19,450
-Was what you did earlier smoking?
-Yes.

816
00:35:19,517 --> 00:35:22,053
It smells really good.

817
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:25,323
-He's taking another bite.
-As he should.

818
00:35:25,389 --> 00:35:28,092
The saltiness of the dish
is also important.

819
00:35:28,159 --> 00:35:29,594
Isn't it bland?

820
00:35:29,660 --> 00:35:32,497
-No, it's perfect to my taste.
-I see.

821
00:35:32,563 --> 00:35:34,665
He successfully smoked the vegetables.

822
00:35:34,732 --> 00:35:37,635
-Then try the Olympic rings.
-The Olympic rings first.

823
00:35:37,702 --> 00:35:40,538
I didn't season it, though.
I wanted you to enjoy the texture.

824
00:35:40,605 --> 00:35:42,006
THE CRISPY OLYMPIC RINGS

825
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:44,942
He's munching on the Olympic rings.

826
00:35:45,009 --> 00:35:47,512
He's eating up the Milano Cortina
2026 Winter Games.

827
00:35:48,112 --> 00:35:50,248
"I will eat up the Olympics!"

828
00:35:50,314 --> 00:35:52,316
-He'll eat it up!
-Yes.

829
00:35:52,383 --> 00:35:53,384
He'll get a medal.

830
00:35:53,451 --> 00:35:55,386
Cha Jun-hwan, the MVP of the Olympics.

831
00:35:56,754 --> 00:35:57,889
It's too bland, right?

832
00:35:57,955 --> 00:36:00,658
No, it's really good.
It's not too bland for me.

833
00:36:01,425 --> 00:36:03,261
Even the Olympic rings.

834
00:36:03,327 --> 00:36:06,764
-Next, with the squid, right?
-Yes, with the squid.

835
00:36:06,831 --> 00:36:08,199
-Cut it up.
-Cut it.

836
00:36:08,266 --> 00:36:11,102
-That's nice.
-He cuts a big piece.

837
00:36:11,169 --> 00:36:13,104
-It cuts very clean.
-How does it look?

838
00:36:13,171 --> 00:36:15,506
Everything is intact.

839
00:36:15,573 --> 00:36:17,575
This is the trunk.

840
00:36:17,642 --> 00:36:19,510
-He takes a big bite.
-That's a big bite.

841
00:36:20,778 --> 00:36:23,848
HIS EYES WIDENED AGAIN

842
00:36:23,915 --> 00:36:25,583
Jun-hwan is chewing on the food.

843
00:36:25,650 --> 00:36:27,218
Is it tough in any way?

844
00:36:27,285 --> 00:36:29,453
-No, not at all.
-It's not tough.

845
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:31,856
It tastes very light because of the tofu.

846
00:36:32,623 --> 00:36:35,159
-I taste shrimp and scallops too.
-Shrimp?

847
00:36:35,226 --> 00:36:38,229
I added shrimp, scallops,
and water parsley.

848
00:36:38,296 --> 00:36:41,933
The balance is great,
and it's very delicious.

849
00:36:41,999 --> 00:36:43,935
It must've been impressive.

850
00:36:44,001 --> 00:36:46,304
Some people don't like the smell
of water parsley. Is it okay for you?

851
00:36:46,370 --> 00:36:47,638
Is this water parsley?

852
00:36:47,705 --> 00:36:48,906
-Yes, water parsley.
-I haven't tried it.

853
00:36:48,973 --> 00:36:50,775
Does he like water parsley?

854
00:36:50,841 --> 00:36:52,743
-It has a good smell.
-It does.

855
00:36:52,810 --> 00:36:54,145
It's good for detoxing.

856
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:55,379
He eats so well.

857
00:36:55,446 --> 00:36:57,648
So? Did it cheer you up?

858
00:36:57,715 --> 00:36:58,649
Yes.

859
00:36:58,716 --> 00:37:00,785
-Is it giving you energy?
-Yes.

860
00:37:00,851 --> 00:37:01,786
That's great.

861
00:37:01,852 --> 00:37:05,890
Next, Chef Ho-young's Cab, Cab, Cabbage.

862
00:37:05,957 --> 00:37:07,959
HE FIGHTS WITH A VARIETY
OF TEXTURES AND FLAVORS

863
00:37:09,327 --> 00:37:12,797
AIMING STRAIGHT FOR A GOLD MEDAL
IN THE UPCOMING OLYMPICS

864
00:37:14,065 --> 00:37:17,268
CHEF JUNG HO-YOUNG'S
CAB, CAB, CABBAGE

865
00:37:17,335 --> 00:37:18,603
Do you like the gold medal?

866
00:37:18,669 --> 00:37:20,938
I love it. It was designed just for me.

867
00:37:21,005 --> 00:37:23,941
I didn't season the gold medal

868
00:37:24,008 --> 00:37:27,211
because I wanted you to get the taste
of a real gold medal in the Olympics.

869
00:37:27,278 --> 00:37:29,447
It's for him to taste it
when he goes to Milan.

870
00:37:29,513 --> 00:37:31,282
These things are so important.

871
00:37:31,349 --> 00:37:32,550
-The story behind it.
-Exactly.

872
00:37:32,617 --> 00:37:34,752
Let's have him taste it.
What's the gold medal like?

873
00:37:34,819 --> 00:37:38,556
It doesn't taste like anything.
He didn't season it at all.

874
00:37:38,623 --> 00:37:40,524
-Wait.
-Hey.

875
00:37:40,591 --> 00:37:43,461
-No flavors.
-He didn't season it much.

876
00:37:43,527 --> 00:37:45,896
Try the gold medal and see how it tastes.

877
00:37:46,397 --> 00:37:47,898
The gold medal made by Chef Ho-young.

878
00:37:50,368 --> 00:37:52,003
Does it taste special?

879
00:37:52,870 --> 00:37:54,839
-It's great with the sauce.
-Yes?

880
00:37:55,406 --> 00:37:58,643
I has a great balance
even though it wasn't seasoned.

881
00:37:58,709 --> 00:38:01,612
-It's seasoned perfectly.
-I see.

882
00:38:01,679 --> 00:38:03,814
You got the gold medal, so let's feast.

883
00:38:03,881 --> 00:38:07,918
I poured some garlic sauce
over the cabbage.

884
00:38:07,985 --> 00:38:11,522
-Try that first, then the fritters.
-Okay.

885
00:38:11,589 --> 00:38:12,890
As for the cabbage…

886
00:38:14,258 --> 00:38:15,293
make sure to get the edge.

887
00:38:15,359 --> 00:38:17,662
-The edge?
-The edge?

888
00:38:17,728 --> 00:38:19,497
You want him to eat the edge?

889
00:38:19,563 --> 00:38:21,866
-You said it wasn't burnt!
-The edges have the most flavor.

890
00:38:22,466 --> 00:38:25,569
The crust is the best part
in mung bean pancakes too.

891
00:38:25,636 --> 00:38:26,871
Cabbage steak. Okay.

892
00:38:27,371 --> 00:38:28,572
A BIG SLICE

893
00:38:28,639 --> 00:38:31,242
Jun-hwan especially loves cabbage.

894
00:38:31,309 --> 00:38:33,678
-He always has it for lunch.
-Yes.

895
00:38:33,744 --> 00:38:35,012
Oh, wow.

896
00:38:35,646 --> 00:38:38,049
-It looks good.
-I think it'll be.

897
00:38:38,115 --> 00:38:39,383
He's taking a bite.

898
00:38:39,884 --> 00:38:40,951
YUM

899
00:38:41,585 --> 00:38:42,920
YUM

900
00:38:43,921 --> 00:38:45,022
Mmm.

901
00:38:45,089 --> 00:38:46,724
His eyes widened.

902
00:38:47,658 --> 00:38:49,860
EYES WIDE OPEN

903
00:38:50,661 --> 00:38:51,662
This is really good.

904
00:38:53,631 --> 00:38:55,166
So this is really good,

905
00:38:55,232 --> 00:38:56,634
but the other one wasn't really good?

906
00:38:57,201 --> 00:38:58,069
DIZZY

907
00:38:58,135 --> 00:39:01,238
They're both sensitive
about every single thing you say.

908
00:39:02,273 --> 00:39:05,710
It became very tender,

909
00:39:06,444 --> 00:39:07,845
so the texture was very nice.

910
00:39:07,912 --> 00:39:12,083
This situation
could strike up a controversy.

911
00:39:12,149 --> 00:39:15,086
The beef looks undercooked.

912
00:39:15,152 --> 00:39:17,121
It's okay to eat it as is.

913
00:39:17,855 --> 00:39:18,723
No, it's…

914
00:39:18,789 --> 00:39:20,324
YUM

915
00:39:20,391 --> 00:39:24,128
Of course, he can eat it as is.

916
00:39:24,195 --> 00:39:28,699
-You'll realize why when you eat it.
-So it's okay?

917
00:39:28,766 --> 00:39:32,069
It would've been cooked to the core
if he had more time,

918
00:39:32,136 --> 00:39:33,337
but it didn't need to be cooked.

919
00:39:33,404 --> 00:39:35,806
-That looks delicious too.
-Right?

920
00:39:35,873 --> 00:39:38,175
He tops it with a piece of cabbage.

921
00:39:38,242 --> 00:39:41,712
The cabbage enthusiast, Jun-hwan.

922
00:39:41,779 --> 00:39:46,484
It's like a quadruple salchow.

923
00:39:46,550 --> 00:39:48,686
Did he succeed or not?

924
00:39:48,753 --> 00:39:50,721
It goes so well with the sauce.

925
00:39:50,788 --> 00:39:53,057
-The sauce must be good.
-Nothing was undercooked, right?

926
00:39:53,124 --> 00:39:56,260
I was a little worried, but…

927
00:39:56,327 --> 00:39:59,196
I tend to like raw beef and beef sashimi.

928
00:39:59,263 --> 00:40:00,698
It worked.

929
00:40:00,765 --> 00:40:03,868
-It's well-balanced with the sauce.
-I'm glad.

930
00:40:03,934 --> 00:40:05,870
You got lucky.

931
00:40:05,936 --> 00:40:09,740
-No one knew he liked raw beef.
-Right? He was so lucky.

932
00:40:09,807 --> 00:40:12,009
On top of that, he had faith

933
00:40:12,076 --> 00:40:14,478
because Ho-young took a bite of that.

934
00:40:14,545 --> 00:40:16,247
Yes, he gave him that faith.

935
00:40:16,313 --> 00:40:19,750
Jun-hwan could eat in peace
after he was reassured.

936
00:40:19,817 --> 00:40:22,253
Let's try Nam-no's dish first.

937
00:40:22,319 --> 00:40:23,687
I was so curious about the filling.

938
00:40:23,754 --> 00:40:25,356
He can give an accurate review.

939
00:40:26,457 --> 00:40:28,192
He tries the squid sundae first.

940
00:40:28,893 --> 00:40:30,795
He wanted to know what it tasted like.

941
00:40:32,229 --> 00:40:33,964
HE GIVES A THUMBS-UP RIGHT AWAY!

942
00:40:34,031 --> 00:40:35,833
You're giving a thumbs-up
while you're chewing?

943
00:40:36,233 --> 00:40:37,468
MMM

944
00:40:37,968 --> 00:40:39,170
I get it.

945
00:40:39,236 --> 00:40:41,672
Okay. He's saying it's so delicious
and tender,

946
00:40:41,739 --> 00:40:43,207
and it's cooked well throughout.

947
00:40:43,274 --> 00:40:45,576
THE FAIRY'S THOUGHTS
WERE INTERPRETED IN REAL TIME

948
00:40:45,643 --> 00:40:46,977
What else?

949
00:40:47,578 --> 00:40:49,947
-And the flavor.
-The flavor was like

950
00:40:50,014 --> 00:40:51,015
he was swimming in the sea.

951
00:40:52,349 --> 00:40:56,287
-Like a squid swimming in the Pacific.
-It makes him sing music.

952
00:40:56,353 --> 00:40:58,689
-It's really good.
-I see.

953
00:40:58,756 --> 00:41:01,459
The shrimp and brisket all became one.

954
00:41:01,525 --> 00:41:03,294
They became one? I see.

955
00:41:03,360 --> 00:41:06,497
World peace.

956
00:41:06,564 --> 00:41:09,633
You were quite worried
about the 15-minute limit.

957
00:41:09,700 --> 00:41:12,703
My heart drops when my guests
ring the bell at <i>Fairy's Table</i>

958
00:41:12,770 --> 00:41:15,039
-before I'm done with the dish.
-I see.

959
00:41:15,105 --> 00:41:16,340
I felt that back there.

960
00:41:16,407 --> 00:41:18,542
It was so hard to deal with
toward the end.

961
00:41:18,609 --> 00:41:20,277
No one was ready when there was
only one minute left in the round.

962
00:41:20,344 --> 00:41:22,079
HIS HEART ALMOST DROPPED
IN THOSE 15 MINUTES

963
00:41:22,146 --> 00:41:23,781
It's not so bad for 15 minutes, right?

964
00:41:23,848 --> 00:41:26,617
It's not just "okay." I'm impressed.

965
00:41:26,684 --> 00:41:29,887
It's simply crazy
for them to cook like this in 15 minutes.

966
00:41:29,954 --> 00:41:33,357
Right? And he tries the cabbage salad.

967
00:41:33,424 --> 00:41:36,794
Yes, he's already frowning.

968
00:41:36,861 --> 00:41:38,529
The torch just went up.

969
00:41:38,596 --> 00:41:39,597
CLENCHING HIS HANDS AGAIN

970
00:41:40,431 --> 00:41:41,532
Did everything become one?

971
00:41:41,732 --> 00:41:43,501
SWAYING

972
00:41:43,567 --> 00:41:45,836
-The world became one.
-That's right.

973
00:41:45,903 --> 00:41:48,506
I find it too greasy
when something tastes too smokey.

974
00:41:48,572 --> 00:41:49,907
I can smell the smoke,

975
00:41:49,974 --> 00:41:55,045
but the sweetness of the cabbage
and peas all jump in

976
00:41:55,112 --> 00:41:58,382
and turn it into a wonderful dish.
I'm truly impressed.

977
00:41:58,449 --> 00:42:00,384
I really wanted to try this too.

978
00:42:00,451 --> 00:42:03,821
Next, it's Ho-young's dish,
Cab, Cab, Cabbage.

979
00:42:03,888 --> 00:42:05,956
That cabbage.

980
00:42:06,023 --> 00:42:09,894
This cabbage was completely
smoked in fire,

981
00:42:09,960 --> 00:42:11,962
but this one brings out the sweetness

982
00:42:13,130 --> 00:42:16,300
-in a subtle and light way.
-A subtle flavor.

983
00:42:17,301 --> 00:42:20,738
Now, try the fritter.

984
00:42:20,804 --> 00:42:22,606
The fritter.

985
00:42:22,673 --> 00:42:24,141
The fritter and the sauce.

986
00:42:25,042 --> 00:42:26,544
Does this deserve two thumbs-up?

987
00:42:26,610 --> 00:42:28,879
The meat might have been undercooked.

988
00:42:28,946 --> 00:42:32,049
I think it was his intention
to undercook the beef.

989
00:42:32,116 --> 00:42:34,718
The ingredients are super crunchy.

990
00:42:34,785 --> 00:42:38,322
Asparagus is a vegetable that doesn't
have to be cooked all the way.

991
00:42:38,389 --> 00:42:41,825
It may not have been as good
if he cooked it longer than this.

992
00:42:41,892 --> 00:42:43,327
-You think so?
-Yes.

993
00:42:43,394 --> 00:42:46,397
-It's really good. The sauce too.
-I see.

994
00:42:46,463 --> 00:42:49,767
Now, it's time to make your decision.

995
00:42:49,833 --> 00:42:52,036
Press one for Yoon Nam-no,

996
00:42:52,102 --> 00:42:54,171
and press two for Jung Ho-young.

997
00:42:54,238 --> 00:42:56,073
Please press the button.

998
00:42:56,740 --> 00:42:59,677
A dish for the Milano Cortina Olympics,
cheer up, baby.

999
00:43:01,545 --> 00:43:03,814
-Jun-hwan!
-Oh, man.

1000
00:43:03,881 --> 00:43:07,318
-He's thinking.
-He's torn.

1001
00:43:07,384 --> 00:43:09,987
Which one gave him more energy?

1002
00:43:10,054 --> 00:43:12,890
-All right.
-This is just…

1003
00:43:12,957 --> 00:43:14,491
-I pressed it.
-This is just… Did you?

1004
00:43:14,558 --> 00:43:17,394
He pressed the button.
Let's find out the winner!

1005
00:43:17,461 --> 00:43:19,997
Which one gave him more energy?

1006
00:43:20,064 --> 00:43:22,399
Cheer up, baby. Will it be Ho-young?

1007
00:43:23,033 --> 00:43:24,602
Will it be Nam-no?

1008
00:43:24,668 --> 00:43:27,605
Who did Jun-hwan choose?

1009
00:43:27,671 --> 00:43:28,906
The winner is…

1010
00:43:34,345 --> 00:43:36,313
YOON NAM-NO WINS

1011
00:43:36,380 --> 00:43:40,250
Yoon Nam-no wins!

1012
00:43:41,151 --> 00:43:43,721
-The squid became the winner.
-The squid.

1013
00:43:43,787 --> 00:43:44,989
What was it called again?

1014
00:43:45,055 --> 00:43:48,559
<i>Fighting Squid</i>

1015
00:43:49,193 --> 00:43:54,131
Fighting Squid wins
despite the controversy over the name.

1016
00:43:54,198 --> 00:43:57,501
What was the crucial difference
between the two?

1017
00:43:57,568 --> 00:44:01,805
I don't think this was
something I could evaluate.

1018
00:44:01,872 --> 00:44:03,674
Both dishes were absolutely delicious.

1019
00:44:03,741 --> 00:44:08,979
But Chef Nam-no's dish was seasoned
in the way that I preferred.

1020
00:44:09,046 --> 00:44:11,048
-He added more salt.
-The salt from before.

1021
00:44:11,115 --> 00:44:14,284
-It was a bit salty.
-The peanut sauce.

1022
00:44:14,351 --> 00:44:15,819
I'm sorry, Ho-young.

1023
00:44:16,720 --> 00:44:18,355
HEAD DROPPED

1024
00:44:18,422 --> 00:44:21,225
-He added too much salt.
-Right?

1025
00:44:21,291 --> 00:44:24,628
I was surprised, too.
He used too much for the performance.

1026
00:44:24,695 --> 00:44:26,730
What happened?
You're so good at seasoning food.

1027
00:44:26,797 --> 00:44:29,333
The next two chefs, you're on your own.

1028
00:44:30,467 --> 00:44:32,670
I wanted to help him out.

1029
00:44:32,736 --> 00:44:35,239
Chef Yoon Nam-no

1030
00:44:35,305 --> 00:44:37,307
receives a star from Jun-hwan,
totaling to two stars.

1031
00:44:37,374 --> 00:44:40,511
Congratulations! That's his second star.

1032
00:44:40,577 --> 00:44:43,147
Congratulations! Nam-no wins.

1033
00:44:43,213 --> 00:44:47,685
This is the second cook-off
with ingredients from Jun-hwan's fridge.

1034
00:44:47,751 --> 00:44:51,588
You're to make a cheat dish for the crazy.

1035
00:44:51,655 --> 00:44:54,792
The craziest chef, Choi Hyun-suk,

1036
00:44:54,858 --> 00:44:59,296
is up against a simply crazy man,
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.

1037
00:44:59,363 --> 00:45:00,931
Not only will I stick to the order,

1038
00:45:00,998 --> 00:45:04,768
but I'll cook as someone
who supports Jun-hwan very much.

1039
00:45:04,835 --> 00:45:06,737
It doesn't matter
what he has in his fridge.

1040
00:45:06,804 --> 00:45:09,173
If he doesn't have anything,
I'll even grill my hands

1041
00:45:09,239 --> 00:45:11,375
-and make sure he's satisfied.
-What's with him?

1042
00:45:11,442 --> 00:45:13,644
That's what I'll keep in mind.

1043
00:45:13,711 --> 00:45:16,647
-He's getting ahead of himself. He is.
-He really is crazy.

1044
00:45:16,714 --> 00:45:20,584
I really enjoyed your program,
"Ballad for the Crazy."

1045
00:45:20,651 --> 00:45:21,852
I even danced with you.

1046
00:45:22,453 --> 00:45:24,722
-I danced like crazy.
-Dancing with him.

1047
00:45:24,788 --> 00:45:26,924
I'll show you what true insanity is.

1048
00:45:26,990 --> 00:45:28,959
I'm the craziest man in this area!

1049
00:45:30,894 --> 00:45:32,863
-Can you make a good cheat day dish?
-Yes.

1050
00:45:32,930 --> 00:45:34,932
Every day is a cheat day for me.

1051
00:45:36,867 --> 00:45:38,602
That's not a cheat day, then.

1052
00:45:38,669 --> 00:45:40,571
Every day is a cheat day for him?

1053
00:45:40,637 --> 00:45:43,107
-I realized cheat days are my life.
-Right.

1054
00:45:43,173 --> 00:45:47,144
I'm a bit worried
because after you eat Poong's dish,

1055
00:45:47,211 --> 00:45:49,613
your feet may get fat,
and you'll no longer fit in your skates.

1056
00:45:50,180 --> 00:45:51,181
A FATAL SIDE

1057
00:45:51,248 --> 00:45:53,884
-It'll make you put on weight.
-Even his feet.

1058
00:45:53,951 --> 00:45:55,219
You can gain weight on your feet.

1059
00:45:55,285 --> 00:45:57,488
Please don't let my feet get fat.

1060
00:45:57,554 --> 00:45:59,556
All right. I'll spare your feet.

1061
00:45:59,623 --> 00:46:01,925
Please spare my feet.

1062
00:46:01,992 --> 00:46:03,193
CHEF HYUN-SUK: VANILLA ICE
CREAM, PENNE, SIRLOIN,

1063
00:46:03,260 --> 00:46:04,194
GALBI SAUCE, CHERRY TOMATO,
MUSHROOM SOUP,

1064
00:46:04,261 --> 00:46:05,596
ABALONE SOY SAUCE, CHEUNG FUN
SAUCE, SEAFOOD STOCK, AND MORE

1065
00:46:05,662 --> 00:46:08,799
My dish is titled

1066
00:46:08,866 --> 00:46:10,234
Crazy Penne.

1067
00:46:10,300 --> 00:46:12,369
-"Crazy Penne."
-Yes.

1068
00:46:12,436 --> 00:46:13,837
-That's his Instagram handle.
-Yeah.

1069
00:46:13,904 --> 00:46:17,274
It's also my social media handle.

1070
00:46:17,341 --> 00:46:19,576
Are you trying to promote that?

1071
00:46:19,643 --> 00:46:21,111
-No, it's not that.
-You're supposed to cook.

1072
00:46:21,178 --> 00:46:23,347
It was heartbreaking to hear

1073
00:46:23,413 --> 00:46:25,616
that Jun-hwan eats
only ten pieces of penne

1074
00:46:25,682 --> 00:46:26,784
cooked in perilla oil.

1075
00:46:26,850 --> 00:46:29,119
I'll show you a crazy penne dish

1076
00:46:29,186 --> 00:46:31,088
you've never had before.

1077
00:46:31,155 --> 00:46:32,089
-I see.
-Crazy Penne?

1078
00:46:32,156 --> 00:46:33,457
He wanted a dish for a cheat day,

1079
00:46:33,524 --> 00:46:37,094
so I'll make something he'll keep craving.

1080
00:46:37,161 --> 00:46:39,163
Seafood crêpe as the appetizer,

1081
00:46:39,797 --> 00:46:44,835
and the main dish is inspired by Milanese,
carbs topped with meat.

1082
00:46:44,902 --> 00:46:48,739
-I'll make those two dishes.
-I see.

1083
00:46:48,806 --> 00:46:51,408
An appetizer and a main dish.

1084
00:46:51,475 --> 00:46:52,643
I am…

1085
00:46:52,709 --> 00:46:54,111
NODDING

1086
00:46:54,178 --> 00:46:56,246
-Write it down.
-…about to…

1087
00:46:56,313 --> 00:46:59,016
-Write it down!
-This place is weird.

1088
00:46:59,082 --> 00:47:00,450
He wants him to write it down.

1089
00:47:01,151 --> 00:47:02,853
-He's so serious.
-I am about to begin

1090
00:47:02,920 --> 00:47:07,457
another battle against myself today.

1091
00:47:08,025 --> 00:47:08,926
I SEE…

1092
00:47:08,992 --> 00:47:12,763
That was a good one.
He'll begin a battle against himself.

1093
00:47:12,830 --> 00:47:13,664
WEBTOON ARTIST POONG:

1094
00:47:13,730 --> 00:47:15,299
CHERRY TOMATOES, SEAFOOD STOCK,
BLUE CRAB LEGS, ABALONE INNARDS,

1095
00:47:15,365 --> 00:47:16,433
BRISKET, OYSTER SAUCE,
CABBAGE, SHRIMP, ENOKI

1096
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:19,436
Today is finally the day

1097
00:47:19,503 --> 00:47:22,372
my battle against Chef Hyun-suk begins.

1098
00:47:22,439 --> 00:47:24,074
-I won't fight against myself.
-Sure.

1099
00:47:24,141 --> 00:47:26,944
-I'm only after Hyun-suk.
-I see.

1100
00:47:27,010 --> 00:47:29,379
-Here's the name of my dish.
-Yes?

1101
00:47:30,347 --> 00:47:34,685
<i>It's C-C-C-C-C-C-C-Crazy Soup.</i>

1102
00:47:34,751 --> 00:47:38,155
<i>C-C-C-C-C-C-C-Crazy Soup</i>

1103
00:47:41,892 --> 00:47:43,193
-Isn't that the song?
-Yes.

1104
00:47:43,260 --> 00:47:45,629
Is that how you sing a 2NE1 song?

1105
00:47:45,696 --> 00:47:48,565
-You do it.
-Watch your attitude.

1106
00:47:48,632 --> 00:47:51,201
I heard everything he said very closely,

1107
00:47:51,268 --> 00:47:54,805
and he said he enjoyed tomato broth
at a hot pot place.

1108
00:47:54,872 --> 00:47:57,774
I heard that and thought, "This is it."

1109
00:47:57,841 --> 00:48:01,411
I'm going to make tomato soup.

1110
00:48:01,478 --> 00:48:03,180
That's such a simple approach.

1111
00:48:03,247 --> 00:48:05,916
He has cherry tomatoes,
so it'll be a piece of cake.

1112
00:48:05,983 --> 00:48:09,019
Also, the order was something
for the crazy,

1113
00:48:09,086 --> 00:48:13,290
so I thought about
what I could do to meet that need.

1114
00:48:13,357 --> 00:48:15,726
Crazy. Razy. Loazy.

1115
00:48:15,792 --> 00:48:18,695
Loach. I decided to make loaches.

1116
00:48:18,762 --> 00:48:21,098
Crazy. Razy. Loazy. Loach.

1117
00:48:21,164 --> 00:48:23,667
-Yes.
-<i>C-C-C-C-C-C-C-Crazy loach</i>

1118
00:48:23,734 --> 00:48:27,738
I wanted to recreate loaches
in sujebi form.

1119
00:48:27,804 --> 00:48:29,339
-Just the form.
-Yes.

1120
00:48:29,406 --> 00:48:33,076
Because Chef Hyun-suk
has continuously used

1121
00:48:33,143 --> 00:48:36,179
fresh pasta to show off his petty tricks.

1122
00:48:36,246 --> 00:48:37,781
-Right.
-"Petty tricks"?

1123
00:48:37,848 --> 00:48:39,917
"Petty tricks"?

1124
00:48:39,983 --> 00:48:42,619
-He won a few times, thanks to that.
-He has.

1125
00:48:42,686 --> 00:48:45,689
-When this happens, I copy him right away.
-I see.

1126
00:48:45,756 --> 00:48:51,061
So I'm going to make loaches that even
Chef Hyun-suk can't even dare try.

1127
00:48:51,128 --> 00:48:52,362
How scary.

1128
00:48:52,429 --> 00:48:55,299
When Kim Yun-a of Jaurim
and her husband were here,

1129
00:48:55,365 --> 00:48:57,968
-you made caterpillars for them.
-Yes.

1130
00:48:58,035 --> 00:49:00,203
That was a huge hit.

1131
00:49:00,270 --> 00:49:02,706
I think today is another day like that.

1132
00:49:02,773 --> 00:49:05,242
I hope the water doesn't get muddy.

1133
00:49:05,309 --> 00:49:08,078
-He's making loaches.
-But it's tomato soup.

1134
00:49:08,145 --> 00:49:10,914
Even in figure skating,
creativity is a big part, right?

1135
00:49:10,981 --> 00:49:13,350
-It's important.
-It's important, isn't it?

1136
00:49:13,417 --> 00:49:16,186
-I love seeing some creativity,
-I see.

1137
00:49:16,253 --> 00:49:18,288
so I'm honestly
looking forward to the loaches.

1138
00:49:18,355 --> 00:49:20,557
-Right?
-He's excited about it.

1139
00:49:20,624 --> 00:49:24,461
It's time to fulfill
the "cheat dish for the crazy" order.

1140
00:49:24,528 --> 00:49:27,464
This man refuses to make
any ordinary dishes.

1141
00:49:27,531 --> 00:49:30,167
The crazy chef, Choi Hyun-suk.

1142
00:49:31,168 --> 00:49:33,470
He's up against the man
refused by the world of chefs,

1143
00:49:33,537 --> 00:49:37,341
the crazy man of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,
Webtoon Artist Kim Poong.

1144
00:49:37,407 --> 00:49:39,343
A fight between two men
who are crazy about cooking.

1145
00:49:39,409 --> 00:49:42,612
Who'll take the title as the crazier cook?

1146
00:49:42,679 --> 00:49:45,415
Let the 15-minute cook-off begin!

1147
00:49:47,117 --> 00:49:48,752
Begin!

1148
00:49:48,819 --> 00:49:50,220
A BATTLE TO DISCERN
WHO'S TRULY CRAZY

1149
00:49:50,921 --> 00:49:53,523
They begin right away. They'll be busy.

1150
00:49:53,590 --> 00:49:56,193
Fifteen minutes won't be enough.

1151
00:49:56,927 --> 00:49:58,695
He already threw in the penne.

1152
00:49:59,363 --> 00:50:01,732
He keeps putting stuff
into the boiling water.

1153
00:50:01,798 --> 00:50:04,935
I'm making seafood broth.

1154
00:50:05,002 --> 00:50:07,204
-Blue crab pieces.
-Crabs and shrimp.

1155
00:50:08,505 --> 00:50:10,640
-Blue crab legs.
-I see.

1156
00:50:10,907 --> 00:50:12,743
GREEN ONION & GARLIC

1157
00:50:12,809 --> 00:50:15,879
Chef Hyun-suk remains calm.

1158
00:50:15,946 --> 00:50:17,914
-A scale.
-He isn't bothered.

1159
00:50:17,981 --> 00:50:19,583
HE'S USING A SCALE TODAY
TO MEASURE

1160
00:50:19,649 --> 00:50:22,019
EGG, ICE CREAM

1161
00:50:22,219 --> 00:50:23,487
SLAM!

1162
00:50:25,589 --> 00:50:28,759
I AM THE CRAZY MAN IN THIS AREA!

1163
00:50:28,825 --> 00:50:30,460
That sound is overpowering.

1164
00:50:31,028 --> 00:50:32,396
SMASH IT

1165
00:50:32,462 --> 00:50:34,131
DESTROYED!

1166
00:50:34,197 --> 00:50:36,033
He's making green onion oil.

1167
00:50:36,099 --> 00:50:38,235
He's trying to make green onion oil.

1168
00:50:38,301 --> 00:50:42,439
Artist Poong always starts with that
no matter what he makes.

1169
00:50:42,506 --> 00:50:43,774
You threw out a lot.

1170
00:50:43,840 --> 00:50:46,843
All his dishes are pretty much
based on Chinese cuisine.

1171
00:50:46,910 --> 00:50:50,113
He always begins with Chinese cuisine,

1172
00:50:50,180 --> 00:50:54,017
but it comes out as Western
or Japanese cuisine.

1173
00:50:54,084 --> 00:50:58,121
-It's a wonder.
-How will the green onion oil turn out?

1174
00:50:59,456 --> 00:51:02,225
-Damn it. The sealing…
-The sealing.

1175
00:51:02,292 --> 00:51:04,694
-Damn it!
-It was sealed.

1176
00:51:04,761 --> 00:51:07,597
2. MAKE GREEN ONION OIL
WITH GARLIC AND GREEN ONION

1177
00:51:07,798 --> 00:51:08,932
COMPOSED

1178
00:51:08,999 --> 00:51:11,802
WHAT'S HYUN-SUK BLENDING?

1179
00:51:11,868 --> 00:51:13,270
What did he put in there?

1180
00:51:13,336 --> 00:51:15,272
He's making crêpe.

1181
00:51:15,338 --> 00:51:16,506
Crêpe batter?

1182
00:51:17,374 --> 00:51:19,042
Did he have milk?

1183
00:51:19,109 --> 00:51:20,677
HE USES ICE CREAM
INSTEAD OF MILK

1184
00:51:20,744 --> 00:51:23,480
He made crêpe batter like that.

1185
00:51:23,547 --> 00:51:28,151
-Chef Hyun-suk isn't bothered at all.
-He won't even budge.

1186
00:51:28,218 --> 00:51:29,853
-He won't budge.
-Two minutes went by.

1187
00:51:29,920 --> 00:51:31,521
Gosh, time flies.

1188
00:51:31,588 --> 00:51:33,090
Something is already boiling over.

1189
00:51:34,091 --> 00:51:35,025
The blue crab.

1190
