1431
01:01:41,798 --> 01:01:44,367
<i>another battle against myself today.</i>

1432
01:01:45,301 --> 01:01:48,971
HE SHAPES THE SIRLOIN STEAK
TO MAKE IT LOOK NICE

1433
01:01:50,506 --> 01:01:54,077
HE CUTS UP THE PENNE

1434
01:01:55,478 --> 01:01:57,413
Chef Hyun-suk is cutting up the penne.

1435
01:01:57,480 --> 01:02:01,384
-In ring shapes.
-He's cutting them into ring shapes.

1436
01:02:01,451 --> 01:02:05,388
It'll give a different texture
compared to the usual penne.

1437
01:02:05,455 --> 01:02:07,090
This will let him eat more.

1438
01:02:07,156 --> 01:02:10,760
-And the texture is different.
-The texture is different.

1439
01:02:10,827 --> 01:02:13,963
The penne looks too ordinary

1440
01:02:14,030 --> 01:02:15,998
after seeing Poong's loaches.

1441
01:02:16,966 --> 01:02:19,702
Will he be able to win?

1442
01:02:19,769 --> 01:02:20,903
11. ADD THE PENNE
TO THE CREAM SAUCE

1443
01:02:20,970 --> 01:02:24,073
-He's now boiling down the cream sauce.
-Right.

1444
01:02:24,674 --> 01:02:27,043
SLAM

1445
01:02:27,844 --> 01:02:30,413
12. COAT CRUSHED SHRIMP
WITH STARCH

1446
01:02:30,480 --> 01:02:31,614
What's that?

1447
01:02:31,681 --> 01:02:34,117
He's throwing in enoki. What's that?

1448
01:02:34,183 --> 01:02:36,185
-Shrimp.
-Shrimp coated in starch.

1449
01:02:36,252 --> 01:02:38,087
He's almost done with the tomato soup.

1450
01:02:38,154 --> 01:02:39,422
You have three minutes.

1451
01:02:39,489 --> 01:02:40,857
You have under three minutes.

1452
01:02:40,923 --> 01:02:42,291
The sauce.

1453
01:02:42,358 --> 01:02:43,326
Take a look at the sauce.

1454
01:02:43,392 --> 01:02:45,261
What's this sauce for?

1455
01:02:45,328 --> 01:02:47,764
-For the steak.
-It's the steak sauce?

1456
01:02:47,830 --> 01:02:49,499
That must be the steak sauce.

1457
01:02:49,565 --> 01:02:51,968
-Can you try that?
-The sauce.

1458
01:02:52,535 --> 01:02:53,536
Oh, no.

1459
01:02:53,603 --> 01:02:56,572
-Can you try that?
-He put those in.

1460
01:02:56,639 --> 01:02:58,107
ALL EYES ARE ON POONG

1461
01:02:58,174 --> 01:02:59,375
What are those?

1462
01:03:00,476 --> 01:03:02,411
Can you taste that?

1463
01:03:02,478 --> 01:03:04,814
You can try that first.

1464
01:03:04,881 --> 01:03:06,582
-I can't try it because of him.
-Please.

1465
01:03:08,184 --> 01:03:09,318
I'll turn around and try it.

1466
01:03:09,385 --> 01:03:10,620
Try it!

1467
01:03:11,788 --> 01:03:15,191
Is Chef Hyun-suk's sauce crazy?

1468
01:03:15,758 --> 01:03:19,562
IS IT CRAZY LIKE THE NAME
OF THE DISH, CRAZY PENNE?

1469
01:03:20,596 --> 01:03:22,465
-It's crazy!
-It is?

1470
01:03:22,532 --> 01:03:24,734
There's this certain smell. What is it?

1471
01:03:25,401 --> 01:03:27,336
-I can't tell what it is.
-I see.

1472
01:03:27,403 --> 01:03:29,572
It's sweet.
I think he added something else in there.

1473
01:03:29,639 --> 01:03:30,506
Is that so?

1474
01:03:31,641 --> 01:03:36,412
12. TOP THE PENNE WITH STEAK
AND SLATHER WITH SAUCE

1475
01:03:36,479 --> 01:03:37,680
And a strawberry.

1476
01:03:38,748 --> 01:03:41,617
13. TOP STEAK
WITH CHOPPED STRAWBERRY

1477
01:03:44,420 --> 01:03:45,855
Right. Rice!

1478
01:03:46,322 --> 01:03:48,891
HE MICROWAVES THE INSTANT RICE

1479
01:03:48,958 --> 01:03:50,960
-Okay, Jung-hwan.
-Yes?

1480
01:03:51,027 --> 01:03:52,795
-Try Poong's--
-Don't talk to me.

1481
01:03:52,862 --> 01:03:55,498
-Poong's tomato soup.
-Don't talk to me.

1482
01:03:55,565 --> 01:03:58,000
-Please try the soup.
-Yes, do that.

1483
01:03:58,067 --> 01:04:01,771
Try the soup. The actual loach soup
is made with ground loaches.

1484
01:04:01,838 --> 01:04:04,173
-This is one extreme job.
-Yes.

1485
01:04:04,240 --> 01:04:06,108
-All right.
-I have a spoonful right here.

1486
01:04:06,175 --> 01:04:08,010
Now, try it!

1487
01:04:10,112 --> 01:04:14,917
Does it taste crazily good?
Or is it just crazy?

1488
01:04:17,720 --> 01:04:19,655
Jung-hwan?

1489
01:04:19,722 --> 01:04:20,957
It's just crazy!

1490
01:04:21,023 --> 01:04:23,459
I see.
You can't eat it in your right mind.

1491
01:04:24,393 --> 01:04:26,162
JUST NOW
HE WIPED THE PLATE

1492
01:04:28,497 --> 01:04:29,932
CHOI HYUN-SUK'S CRAZY PENNE
IS FINISHED

1493
01:04:29,999 --> 01:04:31,934
Chef Hyun-suk is done.

1494
01:04:32,001 --> 01:04:34,337
There's about a minute left.

1495
01:04:34,403 --> 01:04:36,038
You can take your time. Fifty seconds!

1496
01:04:36,105 --> 01:04:38,975
It looks bizarre. He's plating it.

1497
01:04:39,041 --> 01:04:41,210
He's putting it in a bowl.

1498
01:04:41,277 --> 01:04:43,412
-The loaches are sliding out.
-Wait.

1499
01:04:43,479 --> 01:04:46,449
-The loaches are going in.
-It'll go over.

1500
01:04:46,515 --> 01:04:48,684
-It's going in.
-It'll go over.

1501
01:04:48,751 --> 01:04:52,622
-It's so alive.
-It's as if it's alive. It's so alive.

1502
01:04:52,688 --> 01:04:54,223
It's so realistic.

1503
01:04:54,290 --> 01:04:55,758
Don't put in too many loaches.

1504
01:04:56,559 --> 01:05:00,563
Jae-hyung needs to try some too,
so leave some for him.

1505
01:05:00,630 --> 01:05:03,866
-That's good enough.
-Thirty seconds!

1506
01:05:03,933 --> 01:05:04,867
And rice.

1507
01:05:04,934 --> 01:05:06,802
Rice. You need the rice.

1508
01:05:06,869 --> 01:05:09,639
-Did you forget to heat it?
-I did.

1509
01:05:09,705 --> 01:05:11,641
Can you wipe the sides?

1510
01:05:11,707 --> 01:05:14,443
The rice still needs 30 seconds
in the microwave.

1511
01:05:14,510 --> 01:05:16,112
But he has 15 seconds left.

1512
01:05:16,178 --> 01:05:17,713
-Okay, 15 seconds.
-It'll be too raw.

1513
01:05:17,780 --> 01:05:20,383
He's taking it out.

1514
01:05:20,449 --> 01:05:22,285
-Ten, nine,
-Ten, nine,

1515
01:05:22,351 --> 01:05:23,953
-eight, seven…
-eight, seven,

1516
01:05:24,020 --> 01:05:27,089
-You should put it in the soup.
-Six, five, four,

1517
01:05:27,156 --> 01:05:30,326
-three, two, one.
-Three, two, one.

1518
01:05:30,393 --> 01:05:32,662
-Poong is done!
-He's done.

1519
01:05:33,362 --> 01:05:35,564
Gosh, everything is ready.

1520
01:05:35,631 --> 01:05:38,000
He served it without any side dishes.

1521
01:05:38,067 --> 01:05:39,535
Great job, both of you.

1522
01:05:40,836 --> 01:05:43,439
Gosh, I have a headache.

1523
01:05:45,408 --> 01:05:48,277
Poong usually drops people's expectations,

1524
01:05:48,344 --> 01:05:51,113
-then they turn out okay. There's a twist.
-Really?

1525
01:05:51,180 --> 01:05:53,549
I wonder what it'll taste like.

1526
01:05:53,616 --> 01:05:57,386
These dishes for Jun-hwan
are both finished.

1527
01:05:57,453 --> 01:05:59,755
Those crazy 15 minutes have flown by.

1528
01:05:59,822 --> 01:06:02,925
Jae-hyung, you look worried.

1529
01:06:02,992 --> 01:06:06,696
I don't think
I've ever seen anything this crazy

1530
01:06:06,762 --> 01:06:09,165
during a shoot for a TV program.

1531
01:06:09,231 --> 01:06:11,567
-"Have I ever seen this before?"
-Exactly.

1532
01:06:11,634 --> 01:06:14,570
Poong holding up in his red hand

1533
01:06:14,637 --> 01:06:17,440
-the worms… No, what was it?
-Loaches.

1534
01:06:17,506 --> 01:06:20,676
-Worms?
-Aren't they too big to be worms?

1535
01:06:20,743 --> 01:06:22,778
You can't eat worms.

1536
01:06:22,845 --> 01:06:25,881
Have you ever had loaches?

1537
01:06:25,948 --> 01:06:27,116
-Loach soup.
-Have you ever had loach soup?

1538
01:06:27,183 --> 01:06:30,886
People grind up loaches for the soup.
It's never the whole fish.

1539
01:06:30,953 --> 01:06:33,356
Who serves whole loaches like that?

1540
01:06:33,422 --> 01:06:37,793
People call it the Kim Poong magic,
so I'm looking forward to it.

1541
01:06:37,860 --> 01:06:43,666
Chef Hyun-suk finished making his dish
with a minute left to spare.

1542
01:06:43,733 --> 01:06:46,635
Please try Crazy Penne first.

1543
01:06:46,702 --> 01:06:49,138
SEAFOOD CRÊPE
WITH WILD CHIVE OIL

1544
01:06:49,772 --> 01:06:52,842
THE COMBINATION OF STEAK
AND STRAWBERRY OVER CUT PENNE

1545
01:06:53,342 --> 01:06:56,312
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S CRAZY PENNE

1546
01:06:56,879 --> 01:06:58,314
It's in a triangle,

1547
01:06:58,381 --> 01:07:01,083
so cut up the sharp corners and eat it.

1548
01:07:01,150 --> 01:07:03,986
You can relax
and eat without any pressure.

1549
01:07:05,121 --> 01:07:07,456
It's filled with all kinds of seafood.

1550
01:07:08,124 --> 01:07:10,926
A BIG BITE

1551
01:07:12,061 --> 01:07:14,897
It looks like a scene from a drama.

1552
01:07:14,964 --> 01:07:17,233
-He can't help but smile.
-You're right.

1553
01:07:17,299 --> 01:07:20,269
He looks like the male protagonist

1554
01:07:20,336 --> 01:07:23,506
eating at a Western cuisine restaurant.

1555
01:07:23,572 --> 01:07:26,275
He turns it around to take another bite.

1556
01:07:27,443 --> 01:07:30,446
Doesn't he look like a European prince?

1557
01:07:30,713 --> 01:07:32,681
PROUD MOMMY SMILE

1558
01:07:32,748 --> 01:07:36,152
Did you make this oil
with just wild chives and oil?

1559
01:07:36,218 --> 01:07:38,587
Yes, the stir-fry is creamy,
so I thought it'd be greasy.

1560
01:07:38,654 --> 01:07:42,825
So I put fragrant wild chive oil on it
to balance it out.

1561
01:07:42,892 --> 01:07:46,862
The crêpe, seafood,
and the oil work so well together.

1562
01:07:47,797 --> 01:07:53,669
I like crêpes served like a wrap
with chicken and salad fillings.

1563
01:07:53,736 --> 01:07:57,440
But this tastes completely different,
yet it's very delicious.

1564
01:07:57,506 --> 01:07:59,075
I see.

1565
01:07:59,141 --> 01:08:03,879
I keep chewing on something crunchy
once in a while. What is it?

1566
01:08:03,946 --> 01:08:07,950
You said you liked pickled green plums,
so I added it for sweetness and texture.

1567
01:08:08,017 --> 01:08:11,821
That crunchiness really adds
something to the combination.

1568
01:08:11,887 --> 01:08:14,723
You noticed that. You're such a gourmet.

1569
01:08:14,790 --> 01:08:17,860
-I knew it.
-Now, for the main dish.

1570
01:08:17,927 --> 01:08:22,431
The main dish has a different texture
because I cut up the penne.

1571
01:08:22,498 --> 01:08:26,335
You can have the strawberry, steak,
and penne in one bite.

1572
01:08:27,470 --> 01:08:28,938
Try the meat as well.

1573
01:08:29,004 --> 01:08:30,206
EXPECTANT

1574
01:08:30,272 --> 01:08:31,440
Here he goes.

1575
01:08:32,274 --> 01:08:34,844
-Gosh, he eats so well.
-I know.

1576
01:08:34,910 --> 01:08:37,113
-He's eating a lot today.
-But he has to hold back

1577
01:08:37,179 --> 01:08:39,582
for skating and to win medals.

1578
01:08:41,550 --> 01:08:42,985
I wonder what it tastes like.

1579
01:08:43,619 --> 01:08:46,622
I usually just stir-fried it
in perilla oil.

1580
01:08:46,689 --> 01:08:48,724
It's very creamy,

1581
01:08:48,791 --> 01:08:53,129
but the soy sauce and strawberry
balance it out with the tangy flavors.

1582
01:08:53,195 --> 01:08:55,698
I also like this kind of texture.

1583
01:08:55,764 --> 01:08:57,900
The texture became more interesting

1584
01:08:57,967 --> 01:09:02,037
-because he diced the pasta.
-The texture was interesting.

1585
01:09:02,104 --> 01:09:03,806
You should enjoy it
as much as you can now.

1586
01:09:03,873 --> 01:09:05,975
The loaches are waiting for you right now.

1587
01:09:07,510 --> 01:09:09,011
Let me have one more bite.

1588
01:09:10,379 --> 01:09:11,614
He must feel rushed.

1589
01:09:11,680 --> 01:09:13,949
He must be afraid.
He just took a big bite.

1590
01:09:16,385 --> 01:09:18,254
That was the last bite.

1591
01:09:19,021 --> 01:09:20,422
He's taking in all the flavor.

1592
01:09:21,757 --> 01:09:22,825
Next up, Artist Kim Poong's

1593
01:09:22,892 --> 01:09:25,828
<i>C-C-C-C-C-C-C-Crazy Soup.</i>

1594
01:09:27,229 --> 01:09:31,000
SUJEBI IN THE FORM OF LOACHES
SWIMMING IN THE SOUP

1595
01:09:32,468 --> 01:09:35,004
WEBTOON ARTIST KIM POONG'S
C-C-C-C-C-C-C-CRAZY SOUP

1596
01:09:35,070 --> 01:09:38,507
It was a bit spicy at first
when I tried it.

1597
01:09:38,574 --> 01:09:40,543
He still takes a photo of this too.

1598
01:09:40,609 --> 01:09:43,012
-May I take another photo?
-Sure.

1599
01:09:43,078 --> 01:09:44,280
You're going to lift it?

1600
01:09:44,346 --> 01:09:48,050
-He's looking for a loach.
-Good job.

1601
01:09:48,117 --> 01:09:51,187
There are a few loaches going around.

1602
01:09:51,253 --> 01:09:53,222
My gosh. He captured one.

1603
01:09:53,289 --> 01:09:54,723
My gosh. He captured one.

1604
01:09:54,790 --> 01:09:56,959
-Why are you all shrieking?
-Oh, no.

1605
01:09:57,026 --> 01:09:59,061
-Why are you shrieking?
-Oh, no.

1606
01:09:59,128 --> 01:10:03,065
<i>C-C-C-C-C-C-C-Crazy Soup</i>

1607
01:10:03,132 --> 01:10:04,099
I really want to go crazy.

1608
01:10:04,767 --> 01:10:06,135
It doesn't look so bad.

1609
01:10:06,202 --> 01:10:08,170
-He's drinking water first.
-Water.

1610
01:10:08,237 --> 01:10:09,638
The flavors shouldn't mix.

1611
01:10:09,705 --> 01:10:12,107
It can't mix with Chef Hyun-suk's dish.

1612
01:10:12,174 --> 01:10:14,677
Relax and try the solid ingredients,

1613
01:10:14,743 --> 01:10:18,447
-Okay.
-like shrimp, brisket, and cabbage.

1614
01:10:18,514 --> 01:10:20,749
Then try a loach too.

1615
01:10:20,816 --> 01:10:22,985
Have some soup,
then you can dunk rice in the soup.

1616
01:10:23,052 --> 01:10:26,689
-The loaches are just shaped like that.
-Yes, it's sujebi.

1617
01:10:26,755 --> 01:10:28,557
-It's just a symbol.
-A symbol.

1618
01:10:29,625 --> 01:10:30,459
All right.

1619
01:10:31,360 --> 01:10:32,461
GASP

1620
01:10:32,528 --> 01:10:33,429
I'm not sure.

1621
01:10:33,495 --> 01:10:35,598
-Why are you tossing it around?
-I'm not.

1622
01:10:35,664 --> 01:10:39,935
He tries to avoid the loaches,
but he keeps grabbing its head.

1623
01:10:40,002 --> 01:10:41,770
HE CAN'T MAKE HIMSELF
LIFT THE CHOPSTICKS

1624
01:10:41,837 --> 01:10:43,772
-Thank you for the food.
-He's afraid.

1625
01:10:45,407 --> 01:10:46,609
That was brisket.

1626
01:10:47,710 --> 01:10:49,011
Is it cooked well?

1627
01:10:49,078 --> 01:10:50,512
-Yes, I think so.
-Is it cooked well?

1628
01:10:50,579 --> 01:10:53,482
Now, a shrimp.
He checks one after another.

1629
01:10:53,549 --> 01:10:54,883
It looks good.

1630
01:10:57,886 --> 01:11:01,156
It's different from the shrimp
I usually have.

1631
01:11:01,223 --> 01:11:06,195
-He used starch.
-I crushed it and coated it with starch

1632
01:11:06,262 --> 01:11:10,966
and threw it in the soup,
which makes it chewier.

1633
01:11:11,033 --> 01:11:13,902
-Is that the case?
-Yes, it's much chewier.

1634
01:11:13,969 --> 01:11:15,904
-He has a good palate.
-Indeed.

1635
01:11:15,971 --> 01:11:17,339
Try the tomato soup.

1636
01:11:17,406 --> 01:11:19,108
It'll be hard to work out

1637
01:11:19,174 --> 01:11:20,676
-if it's too spicy.
-It'll be too hard.

1638
01:11:20,743 --> 01:11:21,710
HESITANT

1639
01:11:21,777 --> 01:11:23,312
You might gain weight on your feet.

1640
01:11:23,379 --> 01:11:24,613
It looks like good soup.

1641
01:11:25,781 --> 01:11:27,316
The flavor of the soup is important.

1642
01:11:27,383 --> 01:11:28,350
NODDING?

1643
01:11:28,417 --> 01:11:31,620
Does it taste odd? I see.

1644
01:11:32,955 --> 01:11:34,290
-What was that face?
-All right.

1645
01:11:34,356 --> 01:11:35,891
Does it taste like tomato soup?

1646
01:11:38,327 --> 01:11:39,595
Yes.

1647
01:11:39,662 --> 01:11:41,897
It tastes like tomato soup.

1648
01:11:41,964 --> 01:11:43,365
-Okay.
-The important thing.

1649
01:11:43,432 --> 01:11:46,135
-The important thing.
-It's time.

1650
01:11:46,201 --> 01:11:49,972
-He picks up a loach.
-Will he eat it?

1651
01:11:50,039 --> 01:11:51,573
The loach is out.

1652
01:11:51,640 --> 01:11:53,075
It looks like an actual loach.

1653
01:11:53,142 --> 01:11:55,844
It does look like a loach.

1654
01:11:57,046 --> 01:11:59,615
He's trying the loach by itself.

1655
01:11:59,682 --> 01:12:02,484
-He closed his eyes.
-He closed his eyes.

1656
01:12:03,185 --> 01:12:05,654
-He ate the loach.
-He's taking in the loach.

1657
01:12:05,721 --> 01:12:07,489
-All right.
-It's good for you, though.

1658
01:12:07,556 --> 01:12:09,258
It has a strong abalone innards taste.

1659
01:12:09,325 --> 01:12:11,460
Does that mean you don't like it?

1660
01:12:12,261 --> 01:12:14,730
-Does it only taste like innards?
-I like abalone innards too.

1661
01:12:14,797 --> 01:12:17,499
-You do? I'm glad.
-I'm glad.

1662
01:12:17,566 --> 01:12:19,802
-Please try some rice.
-He never eats rice.

1663
01:12:19,868 --> 01:12:21,603
-He's eating a lot today.
-He is.

1664
01:12:21,670 --> 01:12:23,706
He's dunking the rice into the soup.

1665
01:12:23,772 --> 01:12:25,774
He usually splits one energy bar

1666
01:12:25,841 --> 01:12:27,543
-throughout the day.
-The rice looks the same.

1667
01:12:27,609 --> 01:12:29,611
That's all Jun-hwan ate. What's wrong?

1668
01:12:29,678 --> 01:12:31,780
I put the rice in soup,
but the shape is the same.

1669
01:12:32,981 --> 01:12:36,418
-I knew it wasn't microwaved long enough.
-It won't fall apart.

1670
01:12:36,485 --> 01:12:37,886
He has to boil it twice.

1671
01:12:37,953 --> 01:12:40,723
He put the rice in the soup,
but it kept its shape.

1672
01:12:40,789 --> 01:12:43,025
-The rice looks sticky.
-Sure.

1673
01:12:43,092 --> 01:12:46,061
-I hope the rice isn't too hard.
-I hope it's cooked.

1674
01:12:46,128 --> 01:12:48,063
I set the microwave on
for over two minutes.

1675
01:12:48,130 --> 01:12:49,665
He tried the soup with some rice.

1676
01:12:49,898 --> 01:12:51,500
IS IT GOOD?

1677
01:12:51,567 --> 01:12:53,635
Let me try the loach one more time.

1678
01:12:53,702 --> 01:12:56,572
The loach. You must've gotten used to it.

1679
01:12:57,206 --> 01:12:58,240
EVEN THOUGH IT LOOKS LIKE THIS?

1680
01:12:58,307 --> 01:12:59,842
-My gosh.
-My gosh.

1681
01:13:00,109 --> 01:13:02,478
HE CAN'T GET USED
TO THE WAY IT LOOKS

1682
01:13:02,544 --> 01:13:04,079
-They look like gummy worms.
-That's big.

1683
01:13:04,146 --> 01:13:07,216
-He tries it with some cabbage.
-Try it with some cabbage.

1684
01:13:07,282 --> 01:13:10,085
That's it. He finally knows how to eat it.

1685
01:13:12,287 --> 01:13:14,723
-He's hiding the loach.
-He hid it.

1686
01:13:14,790 --> 01:13:17,493
He tries everything together.
This is the important bite.

1687
01:13:17,559 --> 01:13:21,497
Brisket, cabbage, enoki, and loach.

1688
01:13:21,563 --> 01:13:23,999
-It looks really good.
-It does.

1689
01:13:24,066 --> 01:13:25,100
How is it?

1690
01:13:26,135 --> 01:13:27,269
Is it crazy?

1691
01:13:28,437 --> 01:13:29,338
Well…

1692
01:13:30,773 --> 01:13:32,307
He's trembling.

1693
01:13:32,374 --> 01:13:34,276
Is the food crazy? Or is that man crazy?

1694
01:13:35,544 --> 01:13:38,013
-I know something's crazy.
-Something's crazy.

1695
01:13:38,080 --> 01:13:43,318
But the mix of brisket, cabbage,
and enoki all work very nicely.

1696
01:13:43,385 --> 01:13:46,255
-It's even better with the soup.
-I see.

1697
01:13:46,321 --> 01:13:49,124
That's so interesting.

1698
01:13:49,191 --> 01:13:53,729
-Let's try Chef Hyun-suk's Crazy Penne.
-Crazy Penne.

1699
01:13:54,329 --> 01:13:55,731
It's so good.

1700
01:13:57,166 --> 01:13:59,768
The pasta is completely coated
with the sauce,

1701
01:13:59,835 --> 01:14:02,304
so it made the dish even richer.

1702
01:14:03,038 --> 01:14:07,843
It was a great idea to find a new texture
by changing the shape of the pasta.

1703
01:14:07,910 --> 01:14:12,514
The cream sauce tastes much richer
because he cut up the penne.

1704
01:14:12,581 --> 01:14:14,349
Baby Hyun-suk.

1705
01:14:14,917 --> 01:14:16,618
Just as he said earlier,

1706
01:14:16,685 --> 01:14:21,290
it's a dish that made me think that he had
indeed won a fight against himself.

1707
01:14:21,356 --> 01:14:22,724
I won't ask you anymore.

1708
01:14:22,791 --> 01:14:24,293
BANNED FROM COMMENTING ON
HYUN-SUK'S DISHES

1709
01:14:24,359 --> 01:14:25,561
Please try Poong's

1710
01:14:25,627 --> 01:14:28,764
<i>C-C-C-C-C-C-C-Crazy Soup.</i>

1711
01:14:29,398 --> 01:14:30,632
TOSSING

1712
01:14:31,533 --> 01:14:34,503
That's not a real loach, everyone.

1713
01:14:34,570 --> 01:14:37,139
-Why are you acting like this?
-Try some.

1714
01:14:37,206 --> 01:14:40,209
-The loaches are awesome.
-It's kind of cute.

1715
01:14:40,275 --> 01:14:42,377
It's savory.

1716
01:14:43,378 --> 01:14:45,247
It's good.

1717
01:14:46,315 --> 01:14:47,816
I love the smell.

1718
01:14:48,851 --> 01:14:50,152
A SMALL BITE

1719
01:14:51,854 --> 01:14:54,823
JUN-HWAN TAKES ANOTHER BITE

1720
01:14:55,457 --> 01:14:58,560
I like the sourness of the tomato.
It's fresh and tangy.

1721
01:14:58,627 --> 01:15:00,762
It's amazing
how he always makes it taste good.

1722
01:15:00,829 --> 01:15:02,331
It always tastes good.

1723
01:15:02,397 --> 01:15:04,099
I'm in shock.

1724
01:15:04,166 --> 01:15:07,102
-Is it okay? Do you like it?
-Yes, I do.

1725
01:15:07,169 --> 01:15:09,204
Let's say I drank a lot
and got a hangover.

1726
01:15:09,271 --> 01:15:12,975
I'd recover all my energy
if I had this the next day.

1727
01:15:13,041 --> 01:15:15,911
-Right.
-But I might end up throwing up

1728
01:15:15,978 --> 01:15:17,379
because of the presentation.

1729
01:15:19,114 --> 01:15:20,249
THE LOACHES MAKE
THE HANGOVER WORSE

1730
01:15:20,315 --> 01:15:22,351
I had this thought last week as well.

1731
01:15:22,417 --> 01:15:25,587
I think Poong is just amazing.

1732
01:15:26,722 --> 01:15:28,524
Did the loach seem like a loach?

1733
01:15:28,590 --> 01:15:30,626
-It looks too much like it.
-Too much.

1734
01:15:30,692 --> 01:15:33,128
Even this cola tastes like loach.

1735
01:15:34,363 --> 01:15:35,430
It's slippery.

1736
01:15:35,497 --> 01:15:38,333
-I only stayed true to the order.
-Yes.

1737
01:15:38,400 --> 01:15:40,502
-This is right up my alley.
-I see.

1738
01:15:40,569 --> 01:15:43,772
The flavor was somewhere between
tom yum soup and spicy seafood soup.

1739
01:15:43,839 --> 01:15:46,208
It doesn't taste too dry in my mouth.

1740
01:15:46,275 --> 01:15:48,644
He made a smart choice
by using crabs and tomatoes.

1741
01:15:48,710 --> 01:15:51,280
The sour and savory flavors
were perfectly brought out.

1742
01:15:51,346 --> 01:15:54,149
You think he cooks without much care,
but in reality, he cooks with a plan.

1743
01:15:54,216 --> 01:15:56,084
-It's really good.
-I see.

1744
01:15:56,852 --> 01:16:00,489
All right, then.
It's time to make a decision.

1745
01:16:00,556 --> 01:16:02,824
Jun-hwan keeps eating it.

1746
01:16:02,891 --> 01:16:05,861
-It's kind of addictive.
-I get what you mean.

1747
01:16:05,928 --> 01:16:09,264
It makes you keep reaching for it.

1748
01:16:09,965 --> 01:16:12,200
I already had like five loaches.

1749
01:16:12,267 --> 01:16:14,069
Poong may have a chance.

1750
01:16:14,870 --> 01:16:16,672
May I make a comment?

1751
01:16:16,738 --> 01:16:19,908
Oh, he wants to make a comment.
What is it?

1752
01:16:19,975 --> 01:16:22,544
It's really crazy to cut up penne.

1753
01:16:23,645 --> 01:16:27,916
I wanted you to go crazy
for the flavor and the texture.

1754
01:16:28,584 --> 01:16:31,954
I never imagined
I'd do something so crazy.

1755
01:16:32,554 --> 01:16:35,624
Chef Hyun-suk feels anxious.

1756
01:16:35,691 --> 01:16:37,859
Poong's dish was better received
than he expected.

1757
01:16:37,926 --> 01:16:42,998
The fridge owner's choice
is the final answer.

1758
01:16:43,065 --> 01:16:44,299
THINKING

1759
01:16:45,000 --> 01:16:47,970
-Tell him which is which.
-He pressed it.

1760
01:16:48,036 --> 01:16:51,173
-I'm not sure who'll win.
-I can't tell.

1761
01:16:51,239 --> 01:16:53,775
Cheat dish for the crazy.

1762
01:16:53,842 --> 01:16:56,478
Jun-hwan usually follows a strict diet,

1763
01:16:56,545 --> 01:16:59,081
but today, he had crazy dishes
on his cheat day.

1764
01:16:59,147 --> 01:17:01,450
Will it be Chef Hyun-suk's dish?

1765
01:17:01,516 --> 01:17:03,552
Or will it be Webtoon Artist Poong?

1766
01:17:03,619 --> 01:17:07,889
-Which one did Jun-hwan choose?
-Which is it?

1767
01:17:07,956 --> 01:17:10,525
Show us the result!

1768
01:17:10,592 --> 01:17:11,493
The winner is…

1769
01:17:13,128 --> 01:17:14,830
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S
CRAZY PENNE WINS

1770
01:17:14,896 --> 01:17:16,164
Hyun-suk wins.

1771
01:17:18,500 --> 01:17:20,802
-That was close.
-Look at him.

1772
01:17:21,136 --> 01:17:22,738
IT'S ME, CHOI HYUN-SUK

1773
01:17:24,873 --> 01:17:28,910
Chef Poong's dish was really good,
and it was very addictive.

1774
01:17:28,977 --> 01:17:33,682
But pasta and steak
are something I often eat,

1775
01:17:33,749 --> 01:17:37,452
but I never imagined
eating it with strawberries.

1776
01:17:37,519 --> 01:17:39,588
I liked how Chef Hyun-suk brought out
a different flavor.

1777
01:17:39,655 --> 01:17:42,658
-Also, the keyword was "cheat day,"
-Right.

1778
01:17:42,724 --> 01:17:46,094
so I kept wanting to eat more of it.

1779
01:17:46,161 --> 01:17:49,431
You would've looked cool
if you didn't make that last statement.

1780
01:17:49,498 --> 01:17:51,466
-Please edit it out right away.
-Edit it out?

1781
01:17:51,533 --> 01:17:56,204
-Gosh, why were you so scared?
-You were so afraid.

1782
01:17:56,271 --> 01:17:59,908
Jun-hwan chose Chef Hyun-suk.

1783
01:17:59,975 --> 01:18:01,376
Please put a star on him.

1784
01:18:01,443 --> 01:18:03,979
He's now the sole first place
with six stars.

1785
01:18:04,046 --> 01:18:05,580
-Six wins.
-Six wins.

1786
01:18:05,647 --> 01:18:08,850
Hyun-suk takes another step forward.

1787
01:18:08,917 --> 01:18:11,520
-Congratulations on your six wins.
-Thank you.

1788
01:18:11,586 --> 01:18:13,121
This is a party for <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

1789
01:18:13,188 --> 01:18:14,389
A SUDDEN CHEF & MY FRIDGE
FESTIVAL NIGHT

1790
01:18:14,456 --> 01:18:15,624
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

1791
01:18:15,691 --> 01:18:17,292
-Good luck, Jun-hwan!
-Good luck!

1792
01:18:17,359 --> 01:18:19,494
-We present his fridge!
-We present his fridge!

1793
01:18:19,561 --> 01:18:20,662
What's this?

1794
01:18:20,729 --> 01:18:22,264
That shouldn't be in an ordinary fridge.

1795
01:18:22,330 --> 01:18:23,765
We found a premium ingredient.

1796
01:18:23,832 --> 01:18:26,368
That butter is… I love that.

1797
01:18:26,435 --> 01:18:27,969
I got it from France recently.

1798
01:18:28,036 --> 01:18:31,039
-That's kimchi.
-Please stay seated.

1799
01:18:31,106 --> 01:18:32,974
Why do I feel so anxious?

1800
01:18:33,041 --> 01:18:36,078
You must make 12 servings in 15 minutes.

1801
01:18:36,144 --> 01:18:38,513
-Chef Sung-jun is moving quickly.
-He's fast.

1802
01:18:38,580 --> 01:18:41,483
-There's a difference in the speed.
-He's slower than Sung-jun.

1803
01:18:41,550 --> 01:18:43,385
-Shouldn't you turn on the stove?
-Yes, please wait.

1804
01:18:43,452 --> 01:18:45,253
-When will you chop that?
-Please wait.

1805
01:18:45,320 --> 01:18:47,823
It's going to be seasoned.
Please wait a moment.

1806
01:18:47,889 --> 01:18:50,525
Hurry up! Man, this is frustrating.

1807
01:18:51,359 --> 01:18:52,527
This order is for you.

1808
01:18:52,594 --> 01:18:54,596
It's impossible to make in 15 minutes.

1809
01:18:55,430 --> 01:18:57,265
It's a new technique!

1810
01:18:57,332 --> 01:18:58,533
I don't think Sam can do that!

1811
01:18:58,600 --> 01:18:59,601
I can.

1812
01:18:59,668 --> 01:19:01,837
I've come across this a lot in Italy.

1813
01:19:01,903 --> 01:19:03,839
-Sam looks focused.
-The flounder.

1814
01:19:03,905 --> 01:19:06,608
He's pouring it all over.
He used up all this butter.

1815
01:19:06,675 --> 01:19:08,243
I hope the flavor explodes.

1816
01:19:08,310 --> 01:19:09,778
<i>C'est sublime.</i>

1817
01:19:09,845 --> 01:19:10,712
IT'S SUBLIME

1818
01:19:12,748 --> 01:19:14,216
I wonder if he'll like it.

1819
01:19:27,229 --> 01:19:32,033
Subtitle translation by:
Eunsook Youn
